title: chix and rice
directions: Season to taste; mix and pour in large pan.
Add chicken parts and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cabbage salad-bulgaria(salata de varza alba)
directions: Wash the cabbage and julienne. Rub it with salt until soft. Squeeze excess water. Mix with oil, vinegar and salt (if needed).

title: herbed chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Sprinkle pieces with paprika, thyme, marjoram, parsley, onions and salt.
Pour lemon juice on each piece.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil for juicier chicken.
Yields 4 servings.

title: oysterettes
directions: Mix in big bowl.
Put in cake pan.
Place in 250° oven for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Take out of oven and put in brown bag and shake to take off excessive oil.
Store in Tupperware.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes 1 1/3 cups, which is equivalent to one can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut butter into dry mixture. Add the beaten egg and milk.
Form mixture into a ball.
Flour hands, board and rolling pin. Roll dough into a circle about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut circle into 8 wedges.
Prick with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Press triangles very thin.
Roll chicken up in crescent rolls.
Place in baking dish.
Pour soup over rolls and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes covered with foil and 30 more minutes uncovered.

title: mushroomed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and paprika together in a plastic bag.
Shake chicken pieces in bag to coat evenly.
Heat oil in heavy skillet. Brown chicken on both sides, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Stir soup and milk into skillet drippings.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Spread sliced onion over all.
Cover dish and store in refrigerator for 1 hour or longer.
About 1 hour before cooking, remove casserole and let stand at room temperature.
Bake at 375° covered for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: saucy frank dinner
directions: Cut franks lengthwise in quarters.
Melt margarine; saute onion in large skillet.
Stir in soup, tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and Tabasco sauce.
Add franks and simmer 20 minutes.
Arrange hot bow tie noodles around outside edges of a serving dish or platter with edge.
Fill center with frank mixture. Garnish with parsley if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: booster barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook chopped onion and celery until done.
Mix all together.
Simmer and serve.
This recipe belonged to my Mom (Merna Groesinger) and was served at the FFA Stand at the Stephenson County Fair lunch tent in the 1950's.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Grind vegetables using a coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake for 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crunchy brunch cake
directions: Grease cake pan with shortening. Melt margarine in saucepan. Remove from heat and let cool. Combine sugar and cinnamon in bowl. Add nuts to sugar-cinnamon mixture if you wish. Mix until well blended. Using your fingers, dip both sides of biscuits into margarine, then dip both sides into sugar-cinnamon mixture. Place biscuits in pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove biscuits from pan with spatula; serve warm.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine your butter, sugar and eggs until creamy smooth.
Add your flour, soda and vanilla.
The batter will begin to thicken and it should have little white bubbles on the top.
If using hand mixer, put on medium speed and if hand mixing, 350 strokes.
Grease your tube pan or 2 loaf pans, then pour batter a little bit below an inch from the top.
Place pan(s) in the center of the oven.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in the tube pan or 1 hour in loaf pan.
The top should be golden brown and cake tester should be clean.
Let cool in pan for 20 minutes, then turn out on cooling rack.

title: crescent cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread 1 package of crescent rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over bottom layer of crust.
Place second package of crescent rolls on top of cream cheese mixture to form crust. Beat egg yolk and brush on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: mound bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar; spread in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10minutes.
Combine coconut and milk; spread over graham cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together; spread on top of coconut mixture.
Chill until firm. Cut into bars.

title: jiffy barbecue
directions: Heat oil and onion until soft.
Add catsup, water, lemon juice, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper; simmer 15 minutes.
Add chopped meat (cooked) and simmer until ready to serve on buns.
To make 4 recipes = 12 tablespoons = 2/3 cup.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Combine sugar and white syrup and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Add Rice Krispies.
Melt chips and save for topping. Press cereal mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with chip mixture.

title: tex-mex corn bread
directions: Combine flour and cornmeal; set aside.
In another bowl, combine egg, corn, onion, pepper, buttermilk and 1 3/4 cups cheese.
Stir corn mixture into flour mixture.
Pour into a greased 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes or until bread tests done.
Top with remaining cheese and remove from the oven.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Place all ingredients (except egg whites) into saucepan.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture starts to boil.
When thick, remove from heat.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening together until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add half of flour mixture, half of bananas, half the flour mix and then the rest of the bananas. Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for about 1 hour or until tests done.
Cool before slicing.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Shred the lettuce.
Combine the mayonnaise and mustard; spread on the tortillas.
Arrange the bologna and cheese slices on top. Scatter shredded lettuce over cheese and roll up each tortilla like a jellyroll.
Cut into 1-inch slices and, handling carefully, lay flat on a platter.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Add flour, salt and baking powder, sifted together.
Press through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: fried rice with chicken
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add bok choy, snow peas, green onions and garlic; stir-fry 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Remove vegetables; reserve.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in wok.
Add chicken strips; stir-fry 3 minutes or until tender. Thoroughly blend soup mix, water, soy sauce and pepper in small bowl; stir into chicken.
Add cooked rice and vegetables; heat completely through and serve.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Boil milk and rice in a double boiler for 1 1/2 hours.
Beat egg yolks with sugar, salt and spices.
Add to rice mixture.
Pour into baking dish and top with meringue (beat egg whites until stiff, add 2 tablespoons sugar and continue to beat).
Brown in slow oven (300°) for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt.
In a 12-inch skillet brown chicken in hot oil about 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet.
In the remaining pan drippings cook and stir rice, onion and garlic until rice is golden.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, bouillon granules, salt, saffron and pepper.
Bring to boiling; stir well.
Arrange chicken atop rice mixture.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in peas and pimiento; cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy holiday mints
directions: Mix and roll into small balls.

title: no peep beef stew
directions: Layer in Dutch oven and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not peep.
Stir before serving.

title: low-carb fruit and jello salad
directions: Make jello as directed with 1 cup boiling water; stir well. Stir in yogurt, then fruit. (Do not add extra 1 cup cold water.)

title: blueberry and cinnamon pancakes
directions: In a sizeable bowl, mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add eggs, buttermilk and melted butter.
Stir until blended.
Add blueberries.
Preheat the griddle over high heat and add a little oil.
Pour batter on griddle.
Cook until underside is golden, then flip.
Cook until golden.

title: chocolate goodies(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Cream the shortening, adding the sugar gradually.
Add the unbeaten egg, the cream and the vanilla to the sugar and shortening mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Sift the Gladiola once and measure.
Then add the baking powder, salt, soda and cocoa to it and sift again.
Add the flour to the first mixture gradually, blending well after each addition, to form a stiff dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet or pan, and bake in a moderately hot oven for about 10 minutes.
The combination of brown sugar and chocolate in this recipe gives a most unusual flavor, different from that of other chocolate cookies.
This recipe makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy apple cake
directions: You will also need vegetable oil spray.
Do not use vegetable oil spray near an open flame or a heat source.
Read and follow directions on can before using.

title: old henry bars
directions: Mix brown sugar and oats in a bowl.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Shake pieces a few at a time in a plastic bag with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Drop pieces into buttered Bundt or funnel cake pan.
Boil 1 cup brown sugar and 1 stick of oleo about 1 minute.
Pour over pieces.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and form into a roll.
Chill well.
Slice and sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over tops.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 10 minutes.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Mix Roquefort, cream cheese, mayo and egg until well blended. Cut crusts from bread and roll out flat.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix in bowl the flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and spices.
Pour batter in pan.
Pour butter on top.
Do not stir.
Add your favorite fruit (peaches, apples, berries, etc.).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 to 3 loaf pans. Mix potatoes, eggs and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in potato mixture, alternately with water.
Add nuts or raisins if desired.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Cool completely before serving.
This recipe is great for holiday gifts.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain Salad Roni.
Dice finely and add to macaroni the remaining ingredients.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Serve with celery, carrots, raw cauliflower, crackers, etc.

title: cajun fried fish
directions: Mix enough water with mustard to make a thin gravy.
Dip fish in mustard mixture, then coat well with flour.
Cook in hot oil until golden brown.

title: velvet fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate chips and pecans) for 2 to 3 minutes.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the ingredients thoroughly and pour the mixture into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake the pie at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 1 hour or until the custard is firm. Serve with whipped cream or plum jam.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage. Cube cheese and put in crock pot. Add rest of the ingredients and cook until the cheese melts.

title: pearl pudding
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Blend cream cheese and Dream Whip.
Fold in pineapple, fruit cocktail and nuts.
Chill.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt shortening.
Add beef, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until meat is brown and onion tender.
Stir in ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika, mustard and water. Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Blend 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water.
Stir gradually into meat mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Serve over noodles.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift flour and soda and mix.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and spread with filling which has been cooked and cooled.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: In a large pan, put the oil in.
Add the cabbage and small amount of water; stir and cook until the cabbage is fried some. Add onions, peppers, tomatoes and enough water to cover.
Cook slowly for at least 2 hours.
Put enough hot pepper to make it hot.
Add salt to taste.

title: microwave stuffing(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Combine mushrooms, onion, celery and margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave at High (100%) until vegetables are tender, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: microwave fish fillets with grapes
directions: Use microwave.
Sprinkle onions on bottom of plate.
Lay fish fillets over.
Pour wine and lemon juice over fish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add grapes.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Microwave butter or margarine 30 seconds.
Add juices from fish.
Microwave 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds or until thickened.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and cream; pour over fish.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put onions in with hamburger and brown in skillet.
Add tomato juice, salt to taste, white sugar and chili powder or pepper if you wish.
Cook all vegetables until about done before mixing.

title: rice chili
directions: Cook ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
To this mixture, add kidney beans, tomatoes or tomato sauce, whole kernel corn, beef broth, chili powder and sugar.
Let simmer and then add 1/2 cup Minute rice and mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread broccoli in pan. Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise and spread on top. Toss butter & breadcrumbs in small dish then cover soup mixture with buttered bread crumbs. Cover with parmesan cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350 or until broccoli is tender.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all this, adding sour cream last.
Bake in tube cake pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in oven at 200° for 1/2 hour.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add all other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and put into freezer overnight.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Serve with crackers.

title: golden fish puffs
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Place fillets in greased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches. Season with salt and pepper. Beat egg white and 1/8 teaspoon salt until stiff, but not dry. Fold in remaining ingredients; spoon onto fish. Bake, uncovered, 12 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork and topping is puffed and brown.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown pork in shortening in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover during last 30 minutes.
Add additional water if necessary.
Add chow mein noodles to top for the last 5 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers and onions in thick slices; place in a bowl in layers with salt.
Allow to stand 2 to 3 hours, then drain.

title: any kind fruit pie
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt. Mix oleo with flour, sugar and salt until crumbly like meal. Spread over fruit. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: sweet milk sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Alternately add milk mixture and dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or cinnamon sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Store in sealed container.
Very soft cookie.

title: green pepper pie
directions: Boil 2 quarts water.
Cook peppers for 15 minutes.
Drain and arrange in pie plate.
Heat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine onion, 1 cup water and margarine.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add potato flakes, milk and egg.
Mix together.
Stir in cooked sausage to mixture.
Spoon into green peppers.
Put tomato wedges on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Heat milk, water, sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm; sprinkle in yeast.
Beat until smooth the milk mixture, starter and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn once to grease top.
Cover; let rise until double about 1 hour.
Punch down dough; divide into 3 equal pieces.
Form each into a smooth ball.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain off water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sit in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Add salt to flour and cut shortening into flour.

title: sambhar
directions: Bring water to boil and add chick peas and sliced onion. Simmer until chick peas become slightly tender, about 30 minutes. Add tomatoes and green chilies and continue to simmer.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil and fry the ground coriander, cumin and turmeric. Add fried spices to simmering chick peas along with okra or other vegetable.
Add salt.
Simmer until chick peas and vegetables are tender but not mushy.

title: creamy swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving portions.
Season with salt and pepper; dust with flour.
Heat a little oil in a skillet; brown meat on both sides.
Remove meat from skillet and brown onion a minute or so.
Alternate meat and onion in crock.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover and cook.
Serve with fresh parsley or tomato wedge garnish.

title: four seasons cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box, using the 3 eggs. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch oblong glass baking dish.
Punch holes in cake, using handle of a wooden spoon.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Wash, trim and cut fresh beans.
Measure 4 cups and set aside. Combine rice, 1 1/3 cups water and 3/4 teaspoon salt in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, or until rice has absorbed the water.

title: chocolate-banana cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine pudding, milk, whipped topping and vanilla; blend at low speed until well mixed.
Increase speed and beat until thick, about 3 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of mixture into crust.
Layer slices of banana on top; reserve 1/2 of banana for garnishing.
Pour remaining filling into crust.
Chill 2 hours. Garnish with sliced bananas and whipped topping.
Drizzle melted chocolate in design over top.

title: lite cherry squares
directions: Place whole graham crackers in bottom of a 9 x 14-inch pan, covering bottom.
Add second layer.
Spread pineapple over crackers.

title: noe's fish dinner
directions: Put fish on a plate.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
Marinate with lemon.
Cut onion rings.
Put on top of fish.
Set for 15 minutes, then put in a frying pan.
Deep fry in oil.
Done when it is golden brown on both sides.
Ready to eat with desired side dish.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown together onion, garlic and 1 tablespoon oil.
Add hamburger and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir until completely cooked. Add mushrooms, tomato sauce, tomato paste, oregano and water. Simmer together for 45 minutes or longer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; drain well.
Remove stems and chop.
Saute onions and stems in margarine; add garlic powder.
Stuff mushroom caps with sauteed mixture and bake on cookie sheet until golden brown.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Crumble ground beef in margarine.
Add onion and celery; saute for about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes; break with a fork.
Add water, beans with liquid, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cabbage; cook until cabbage is tender, 15 to 30 minutes, depending on how tender you like cabbage.
Delicious with corn bread.
Freezes well.

title: neiman-marcus dip
directions: Mix cheese, crumbled bacon, onions and mayonnaise together.

title: shrimp spread or dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend for 30 seconds on high speed.
Use with crackers or potato chips.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased 12 x 18-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Beat eggs and oil in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice.
Mix pineapple and marshmallows. Let set overnight.
Mix in a saucepan the egg, pineapple juice, sugar, flour and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Stir often, then let cool.
Mix the Cool Whip, pineapple and marshmallow mixture and egg mixture.
Add apples and peanuts.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Store in glass jar.
Pour over salad before serving.

title: pecan pie with pudding mix
directions: Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix everything except shrimp.
Add shrimp last.
Spread on crackers.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Slice wieners into bite-sized pieces.
Stir mustard and jelly together in crock-pot.
Stir in wieners. Simmer in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours. Serve hot.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken.
Drain and reserve broth.
Pick meat off chicken. Place meat in broth in large soup pot, then add onion, celery and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Then reduce the heat to medium.
Then add salt, pepper, parsley and egg noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: pizza roll-ups
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain.
Remove from the heat.
Add tomato sauce, Mozzarella cheese and oregano.
Mix well.
Separate crescent dough into eight rectangles, pinching seams together.
Place about 3 tablespoons of meat mixture along one long side of each rectangle.
Roll up, jelly roll style, starting with a long side.
Cut each roll into three pieces.
Place, seam side down, 2-inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: calio cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar to stiff meringue; gradually add sugar and M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Put 1 piece of candy on top of each cookie before baking.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine apples and eggs.
Add oil and sugar, mix well.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; add to apple mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon batter into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pan on a wire rack.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Pull off bones and place in bottom of flat casserole dish.
Then spread can of cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Mix egg with broth from chicken and spread over soup and chicken.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream butter in bowl; add sugar.
Beat at medium speed.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: little applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in applesauce.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture; stir just enough to moisten.
Spoon into small muffin cups.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
While still warm, dip in melted butter and roll in the cinnamon-sugar mix.
Yields approximately 30 miniature muffins.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: You can usually find blackberries near gardens or fields. After picking them, take them to the sink and wash 4 times or until bugs are gone.
Put berries in steel pan with 1 quart water and bring to a full boil.
Let berries cool, then squeeze out juice. Ready for jelly.

title: layer bars
directions: Pour butter into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle a layer of crumbs over the butter, then sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, then nuts.
Pour milk over all and spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares while warm.

title: potato casserole ii
directions: Mix together in a large casserole greased with the melted butter. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°. Stir once.

title: green bean-chicken casserole
directions: Skin and cook chicken and debone into pieces.
Cook rice. Place chicken in a 2 1/2 qt baking dish.
Spread rice on top of chicken, add mushrooms, chestnuts, beans, salt, and pepper.
Pour broth over beans.
Dot with butter.
Bake on 325° for about 45 min. to 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: brownie ice cream cake
directions: Line bowl with Saran Wrap leaving a generous overlap.
Work quickly.
Break up brownies on bottom of bowl and sprinkle with walnuts.
With hands, pack down some ice cream well.
Keep repeating this.
Cover with Saran Wrap completely to make it airtight.
Freeze for at least 24 hours.
Invert bowl onto plate and apply hot towels to loosen, then pull off plastic wrap as ice cream softens.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cake
directions: Mix all together and make not too dry of mix.
Put in cake pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until done.
While cake is still hot, put peanut butter on top for icing.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Drain whole peppers.
Slice in half, removing seeds and inner membrane.
Mix cream cheese, onion, garlic and cheese together in a small bowl.
When completely mixed, spoon mixture (stuff) into jalapeno halves.
Place in shallow pan and broil until cheese just starts to melt.
Serve warm or put in refrigerator and serve cold. These are hot!

title: harvest vegetable casserole
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook onions and green peppers until browned, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 1/2-quart casserole, combine barley, bouillon and 1 cup of water.
Add carrots, tomatoes, zucchini, green beans, peas and cauliflower, then onion mixture.
In a cup, combine lemon juice and garlic; pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until barley is cooked.
Makes 12 servings.

title: boned chicken
directions: Line pan with beef.
Wrap each chicken piece in a piece of bacon.
Lay those over beef.
In saucepan, combine sour cream and soup. Mix and pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for three hours.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans; press into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pea soup
directions: In large pot, combine peas, water, ham shank, onion, chicken bouillon and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Remove ham shank; trim meat off bone and return meat to pot.
Stir in carrots and celery.
Simmer, uncovered, until whole peas are tender or split peas have desired thickness.
Remove bay leaf. Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine water, oats, oleo, salt and molasses.
Cool.
Add yeast and mix well.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour gradually and mix well.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Turn out on floured board.
Shape into 2 loaves; place in large loaf pans, greased.
Let rise again. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together and pour into a buttered dish.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding with milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in cookies and either of the chips or granola bars into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Store remaining pie in freezer.

title: szegedi sauerkraut
directions: Chop onion and saute in oil until brown; let cool.
Add paprika and small pork and salt, drained by squeezing sauerkraut. Mix with onions and pork.
Add enough water to cover top.
Put on lid and let it simmer about 45 to 60 minutes.
Checking occasionally, stirring and if all is gone, add a little bit.
Pork and kraut will be tender.
Serve with sour cream on the side (if so desired).
It adds to a very good dinner.

title: quick-fix vegetable mix
directions: Mix all 3 cans together (do not drain).
Season to taste and heat for 5 - 10 minutes.
Serve with cornbread as soup or vegetable stew.

title: "best ever" coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together over raisins, candied fruits and pecans to coat well.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and sour cream and candied fruits, etc.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt cake pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until done (test).
Cool in pan 1 hour before turning out.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Ready to serve in about 2 hours.

title: shrimp supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute mushrooms in butter; spread on bottom of 1 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with halves of deviled eggs; arrange shrimp on top of eggs.
Fold 1 cup grated cheese into white sauce; pour this sauce over all and sprinkle with remaining cup of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: onion - roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake, or toss in bowl, until evenly coated.
In 13 x 9 inch baking pan, arrange potatoes; discard bag.
Bake uncovered, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.Makes about 4 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Set aside 8 large strawberries with greens for garnish.
Stem and slice remaining berries; drain off juice.
Add rice, sugar and vanilla to sliced berries.
Whip cream until very stiff; set aside 1/3 of cream for garnish.
Mix remaining cream and marshmallows to strawberries; mix well.
Spoon into dessert dishes to 3/4 full. Top with 1 tablespoon reserved cream and whole strawberry. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: chicken - broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Broccoli can be chopped.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 375° for 30-45 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole(good)
directions: Add carrots, minced onion and potatoes, ground.
Bake until done.

title: ms. icie's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease skillet or muffin pan.
Place corn meal in large mixing bowl.
Stir egg and milk into the same bowl.
Mix these ingredients very well.
Add vegetable oil and sugar.
Stir until batter is pourable.
Pour batter into prepared skillet or pan.
Bake for 35 minutes or top surface is golden brown.
Yields 8 servings per mixture.

title: taralle
directions: Sift flour into large bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Make well in center.	Add
water,
fennel
seed, oil and yeast; mix well. Turn dough onto table;
knead about 20 to 25 minutes to macaroni dough consistency.	Form
into
loaf.
Divide
into 3 parts and place in bowl
or pot;
cover.
Let dough rest about 15 to 20 minutes or more.
Cut off small pieces and bake about a dozen coils.
Form
pretzels
shape; press ends down.
Place in fast boiling water
for about 1 minute.	Remove immediately when they float.
Place
in
colander
in
cold water.
Remove colander from water.
Place
taralles on clean cloth.
Bake on open oven rack at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large kettle for about 30 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Put in ovenproof dishes and put in oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until thickens. Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour into hot sterilized 1/2 pint or pint jars.
Seal in boiling water bath for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: very best seafood chowder
directions: Steam open clams in a small amount of water.
Dice or grind the clam meat and reserve the clam liquor.
Dice onions, mince garlic and put both into a large kettle with the oil.
Saute slowly until they just barely begin to brown.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
When the onions and garlic are ready, add clam liquor, tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil, oregano, potatoes and water to the kettle and simmer for 20 minutes or until potatoes are just done.
Cut fish into 1-inch pieces and add with the shrimp, scallops and clam meat to the kettle.
Simmer 10 minutes more, stirring a few times gently, so as not to break the pieces of fish. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot with a crusty bread and an assertive red wine.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove bones, gristle,	fat
and skin from cold, cooked chicken.
Cut meat into 1/2-inch
cubes
and
mix
it
with an equal amount of celery which has been scraped, chilled and cut in small pieces.
Moisten
with
French
dressing.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing to taste.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Heat up the cans
of broth and pour over the croutons.
Fry hamburger; grate the apples and add to the croutons.
Mix everything together.
You can boil the liver from the turkey and mash it up and put in the stuffing.
If you need more liquid, use either the broth from the liver or hot water.
Crumble up a package of either hot dog or hamburger buns to add to it.
Mix everything together and bake at 375° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven brown potatoes(firehouse potatoes)
directions: Clean potatoes with cold water.
Mix in a pan with salt, pepper, paprika and onion flakes.
Place potatoes into a deep dish pan with a 1/2 pound of butter.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.
Take pan out of the oven and turn over into a new pan.
Place back into oven at 450° for another hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients in order. Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly and pour in buttered casserole dish.
Mix remaining set of ingredients well and sprinkle over top of the potato mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sally lunn
directions: Scald milk and add fat.
When fat melts, cool to touch. Crumble in yeast; add beaten eggs, sugar and salt.
Mix well and stir in flour.
Beat thoroughly.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down; spoon into greased 9-inch ring mold or pan and let double in size again.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: boiled shrimp supper
directions: Combine water and seasoning in large kettle; bring to boil. Add vegetables; return to boil and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook, stirring, for 3 to 5 minutes, or until shrimp turn pink.
Drain mixture; remove seasoning bags.
Serve immediately with lemon wedges and cocktail sauce.
Serves 4.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In 7-quart sauce pot, mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Cover with cold water and ice cubes; let stand 3 hours.
Drain; rinse well and drain again.
Set aside.

title: marzette
directions: Cook noodles; set
aside.
Cook
the
celery and onion. (You may add 1/2 mango.)
Brown	the
meat
and add the tomato juice; simmer 1/2 hour.
Mix
the	noodles,
celery, onion and meat.
Add mushroom
pieces,
curry
powder and Worcestershire sauce.	Add peas.
Put in casserole and top with grated cheese (Parmesan Italian) and crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: microwave salmon loaf
directions: Beat egg slightly and mix with remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pack salmon mixture firmly in greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch microproof loaf pan.
Cover with waxed paper; cook on 70 (Roast) for 25 to 30 minutes or until loaf is firm.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: crab salad dinner waffles
directions: Put crabmeat in large salad bowl; using fork, toss with scallions, chives, lemon juice, mayonnaise and ketchup until blended.
Season with salt, pepper and Tabasco, can add more lemon. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside.
(Can make this part ahead and refrigerate for a few hours.)
Just before serving add tomatoes to crab mix.
Serve on top of hot waffles placed on a large lettuce leaf.
Can also be served alone.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish and bake 350° until tender.

title: a grand leg of lamb
directions: Dry leg of lamb and spread out, fat side down on a flat surface.

Combine breadcrumbs, melted butter, lemon rind, herbs, nutmeg, capers and 2 or 3 anchovies; toss until well blended. Spread stuffing over lamb, roll up and tie securely with string. Place lamb in a shallow roasting pan, pour wine over it, sprinkle with salt and pepper and roast in a 400° oven for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and roast from 1 1/2 to 2 hours (depending on whether you prefer lamb slightly pink or well done), basting every 20 minutes with juices that collect in the pan.
When lamb is cooked to taste, remove to a heated platter and let stand for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, skim as much fat as possible from pan juices. Place pan over moderate heat and stir to smooth out juices; add water or more wine if more sauce is needed.
Add 1 or 2 chopped anchovies, stir and taste to see if salt or pepper is needed. Garnish the lamb with watercress, toast points, eggs and sausages. Serve sauce in a small heated bowl.

title: crowd pleasin' macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, blend mayonnaise, salt and basil.
Add macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Toss gently. Makes 12 to 26 servings.

title: parmesan spinach balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine spinach, bread crumbs, Parmesan, celery, onion, hot pepper sauce, nutmeg and eggs.
Mix well. Shape spinach mixture into balls using 1 level tablespoonful of mixture for each ball.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, heat 1 1/4-inches oil (approximately 3 cups) to 350°.
Deep fry balls in small batches 1 minute or until golden brown. Remove with slotted spoon. Drain on paper towels. Serve.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes (top of cookies will look pale).
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute, then remove.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Save
cup
chow
mein
noodles until after cooking. Combine ingredients.
Cook 1 hour in a 350° oven.
If need more liquid, use more water of soup.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Place broccoli and chicken in a casserole dish, layered with broccoli on bottom.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter; pour over crumbs and toss.
Spread crumbs and cheese evenly over all.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook on medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring.

title: frozen dessert
directions: In mixing bowl mix pie filling and Eagle Brand milk.
Add pineapple that has been drained.
Fold in Cool Whip until well mixed.
Pour into molds.
Let freeze until firm.
Take out of freezer just before serving.
Keeps a long time in freezer.
Freeze uneaten amounts.
Makes 14 nice slices or can be spooned.

title: garden vegetable appetizers
directions: Roll
out crescent rolls and flatten onto a large baking sheet, pressing down to flatten.
Brown as per directions.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, 1 teaspoon dill weed and 1/2 teaspoon Mrs. Dash until well blended.
Spread mixture on cool rolls.

title: tent burgers
directions: Make patties with hamburger meat. Stuff onion slice in the middle of each patty.
Sprinkle both sides with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Put each patty in a piece of aluminum foil with several potatoes.
Douse with Worcestershire sauce real good. Wrap the patty with potatoes and seal foil.
Put all wrapped patties on a cookie sheet and bake in oven at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: apple juice frost
directions: Combine apple juice, ground cinnamon, nutmeg, cinnamon sticks and lemon juice.
Add ice cream and ginger ale just before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese mix with dressing mix and chopped, dried beef.
Roll into ball.
Let it harden, then roll it in pecan pieces.

title: shrimp mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly over the bottom of a medium to large tray.
Pour the cocktail sauce over the cream cheese. Sprinkle the tomatoes, onion, green pepper and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken with orange sauce
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle pieces of chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat butter; saute chicken until lightly browned on both sides.
Remove chicken; arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.

title: walk to school cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into balls about the size of small walnuts.
Flatten balls with tumbler dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: hot cheese chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: oil pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Pour oil and water into cup.
Add to flour.
Stir lightly with fork.
Press the dough out and up sides of pie pan to form a shell.

title: cottage cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Arrange 1/2 of noodles in greased casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 of cottage cheese over noodles.
Place 1/2 of American cheese slices over cottage cheese.
Pour 1 can sauce over cottage cheese, salt and pepper.
Repeat another layer with rest of ingredients.
Dot with butter.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: twinkles
directions: Bake according to box directions in small loaf pans.
Cool. Split in half-lengthwise.

title: prince of wales pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and sweetened condensed milk in a saucepan over low-medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir constantly for 7 minutes until thick, watch carefully, as mixture scorches easily.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Wait 1 minute until chips have melted slightly.
With a fork, gently swirl the chocolate chips making a pretty pattern.
Chill until firm. Top with dollops of whipped cream and place pecan half on each dollop.

title: hot italian roast beef sandwiches
directions: In a Dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat.
Brown roast on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients except rolls.
Cover and simmer until the roast is tender, about 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Add additional water, if necessary, to keep roast simmering in broth.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, combine soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish and blend well.
Set aside.

title: cavatini
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven brown the beef.
Prepare noodles as package directs.
To the beef add onions, mushrooms, garlic, pepperoni, green peppers, Ragu, tomato sauce and tomato soup.
Serve with noodles.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar; add eggs and flavorings, beating after each egg.
Add 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup milk; beat, then add last 2 cups of flour and remaining milk.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Place ingredients in layers in a 2-quart baking dish with a tight fitting lid.
Start with rice; cover with corn; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water. Add onion and green pepper, crumbled, uncooked ground beef and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover with strips of bacon cut in half.
Cover casserole and bake for 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes until bacon is crisp.

title: cheese things
directions: Mix all ingredients except the tortillas.
Spread mixture on tortilla.
Roll tight.
Wrap and store in refrigerator for 2 days before serving.
Slice and serve.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except almonds. Spread in ungreased 8-inch square pan or dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
(Refrigerate leftovers.)
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: new orleans praline
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently until dissolved.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash sugar crystals from side of pan. Cook to soft boil stage or 235° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat with wooden spoon until mixture begins to thicken.
Work quickly, dropping by tablespoon onto greased waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.
Wonderful.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into very small pieces.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Best
if
refrigerated
a few hours at least before serving.

title: special deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves, lengthwise.
Slip out yolks; mash with a fork.
Mix in remaining ingredients; refill egg whites.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until chilled (1 to 2 hours). Roll into balls, dip in sugar, flatten with bottom of glass onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 7 to 8 dozen.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Stir together salad dressing, soy sauce, ginger and pepper. Set aside.
Heat oil in wok or large heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry for 4 minutes (add water if dry).
Add carrots and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Add rest of vegetables and garlic; stir-fry 3 or 4 minutes or until crisp and tender (add more water if needed, but cook until water is gone).
Stir in salad dressing mixture and simmer 30 seconds. Serve over rice.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: In crock-pot, mix salt, sugar and mustard.
Add molasses and mix.
Add water and mix.
Add washed beans and salt pork.
Cook on low all night and the next day.
Start after dinner Friday night and they will be ready for Saturday night.
Check for water Saturday morning and stir.
Serve with hot dogs and cole slaw.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: Combine hot water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in a large mixing bowl; stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm water mixture.
Add egg and 2 1/2 cups of the flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour and beat
1 minute.
Dough will be soft.
Place dough in greased bowl; brush top with soft shortening.
Cover tightly with wax paper or aluminum foil.
Store in refrigerator until doubled in bulk.
(Dough may be kept 1 week in refrigerator at about 40° to 45°.)

title: eggs with artichokes
directions: Finely mince onions using half of the tops also. Cut artichokes in thirds and reserve oil. Saute onions and garlic in the artichoke oil. Combine all ingredients. Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 as a main dish. May be prepared ahead and refrigerated, then heated 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut into 2 inch squares. Tripled makes 9 x 15-inch casserole and serves 25 to 30.

title: mystery pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk. Add nuts and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into graham cracker crust. Makes 2 pies. "Yum yum."

title: cucumber-pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water (drain).
Drain pineapple chunks.
Reserve 1/2 cup syrup.
Combine 1/2 cup pineapple syrup, mayonnaise and salt. Mix.
Pour over rotini.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer small pieces of lettuce, 1 cup chopped celery, green pepper and green onions.
Top with dressing made of sour cream, mayo and sugar.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.

title: nacho dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on low, stirring occasionally, and serve with corn chips.
Must keep this dip warm or it will get hard.

title: taco dip
directions: Place softened cream cheese in the bottom of glass baking dish (8 x 11-inches).
Add jar of salsa and spread over cream cheese. Top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Soak chicken one hour in egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs and fry in butter.
Place in casserole dish the chicken and mushrooms; cover with cheese.
Baste with broth or lemon juice. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Cover with salt and water 24 hours.
Drain and put alum size of walnut.
Cover with boiling water, spices and vinegar.
Boil and pour over pickles.
Do this 4 days (just heat juice).

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into small balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning often, until brown, about 20 minutes.
(Or bake in oven in 9-inch, oblong pan at 400° until light brown, about 20 or 25 minutes.)

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange congeal salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Add pineapple.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients together, except the pork chops, in a bowl.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on the outside of each pork chop, then stuff the pocket of each with the meat dressing and place in a greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: nora's ham and cheese roll
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add yeast and stir.
Let stand 20 minutes.
In separate dish, mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture and let rise in a warm place for 2 hours.
Spread out half of the dough, adding flour as needed.
Top with sliced ham and cheeses.
Repeat with other half of dough.
Roll up each half jelly roll style.
Let rise 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly and slice.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place chicken breasts in large pot with water.	Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is completely done. Remove chicken from broth and place on plate to cool.
In separate pan saute onions, celery, and garlic in olive oil a few minutes. Do not brown.
Remove chicken from bones and shred. Return shredded chicken to broth.	Add sauteed onion mixture.
Add salt, pepper, and noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: old miss coffee cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour batter into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle nuts evenly over both cakes.
Combine syrup and cinnamon and drizzle over both cakes.
Return to oven and bake another 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large bowl with fork, mix 1 1/4 cups flour and 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add 1/2 cup butter or margarine, milk, egg and vanilla.
With spoon, beat until well mixed.
Pour batter evenly in baking pan.

title: mini reese's cup cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and peanut butter.
Stir in salt, sugars and eggs.
Stir well.
Stir in flour and baking soda.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Bake in muffin pans.
When done, put one Reese's cup in top of cookie after taking from pan.
Hershey's Kisses can be used.
Let cool.

title: cheese delight
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and softened cheese.
Add flour and salt.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press peanuts into each dough ball.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable cream cheese ball(appetizer)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and 1 cup chopped nuts in mixing bowl; mix until well blended.
Shape into a ball.
Roll cheese ball in remaining nuts until well coated.
Yields 1 cheese ball.

title: quick bread and butter pickles
directions: Drain dill pickles in colander for about 1 hour.
Place in stainless steel bowl or Corning Ware dish.
Put sugar, Tabasco and garlic over pickles and stir until it starts to form liquid.
Stir every 1 to 2 hours during the day.
(Keep covered with plastic wrap.)
Let them sit out overnight.
The next day make sure all sugar is melted.
If melted well, put them back into the jar. Pour liquid over them and refrigerate.
They are delicious!

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into twenty 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, about 20 minutes. Or cook in an ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, in a 400° oven until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp cantonese
directions: Heat oil in frying pan or wok until hot.
Add salt and garlic. Cook for 1 minute being careful not to let garlic burn.
Add shrimp.
Remove shrimp as soon as they turn pink in color.
Remove and discard garlic.
Add ground pork to pan and cook until pork is white in color.
Add chicken broth, pepper, sugar, soy sauce and sherry.
Stir and let come to a boil.
Return shrimp to pan; stir-fry to mix.
Add cornstarch mixture to thicken gravy.
Pour beaten egg over shrimp and stir-fry just until egg is set.
Stir in sesame oil.
Sprinkle cut green onions on top and serve over rice.

title: german style potato salad toss
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble. Into 1 tablespoon drippings add onion and cook until tender.
Add potatoes, bacon and Italian dressing.
Toss lightly until coated and heated through.
Serves 8.

title: macaroons
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and salt. Add eggs and beat. Add oatmeal and other dry ingredients. Bake at 350°.

title: beans with celery bacon sauce
directions: Place beans in a large saucepan and cover with water, bring to a boil.
Cook uncovered for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain and set aside.
In a skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp.
Remove to paper towels, drain, reserving 2 Tbsp drippings.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Stir in soup and milk until blended-heat through. Spoon over beans. Sprinkle bacon over top.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown rice in saucepan with cooking oil on medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover lightly and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until rice has absorbed all liquid.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy. Flavor with love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith.
After pouring all these things into your life, bake it with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile anytime and it will satisfy the hunger of starving souls.

title: eggplant and zucchini casserole
directions: Trim ends of eggplants; do not peel them.
Cut into 3/8-inch cubes.
There should be about 4 cups.
Trim ends of zucchini; do not peel.
Cut into 3/8-inch cubes.
There should be about 4 cups.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together.
Grease pan and work dough out in pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pastry and tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Separate into balls and can be refrigerated or frozen for later use.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and cream them.
Add all the other ingredients to the potatoes.
Mix well.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter and chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix sugar, cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.
Melt butter and peanut butter.
Pour over coconut mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate pieces and shortening.
Spear balls with toothpicks and dip into chocolate.
Remove and put on wax paper and chill.

title: ham and cheese sandwich in foil
directions: Make dressing of first 5 ingredients and spread on both sides of buns.
Place ham and cheese on bun; wrap lightly in foil and place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Slice vegetables.
Cut chicken up.
Heat oil in pan.
Cook chicken until done.
Pour lemon juice over chicken; remove when tender.
Add vegetables.
Add soy sauce and cook 2 more minutes. Serve over rice.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water; let set in refrigerator until it starts to jell.
Add rest of ingredients and serve with Cool Whip.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Push chopped pecans into thawed crusts and bake.
Warm cream cheese to room temperature and mix with Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla.
Divide this mixture into cooled pie shells.
Pour cherries on top and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Cook as directed on package; drain.
Place in oblong baking dish.
Add soup (undiluted).
Spread sour cream on top.
Spread Durkee onion rings on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grilled teriyaki pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour half of this mixture into a large dish.
Place chops in mixture; pour remaining mixture over chops.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight, turning meat occasionally.
Grill chops over medium to low direct heat until brown.
Turn meat.
Brush with marinade mixture.
Remaining mixture is great over cooked white rice.

title: menudo
directions: Cut tripe into small pieces.

Cut pigs feet in 2-inch pieces if they have not been sliced through the middle by the butcher. Put meat in a large pan with about 1 gallon of water and simmer together with salt, garlic and cilantro for about 4 hours or until tripe and pigs feet are tender.

title: tiny tims
directions: Marinate fruits and nuts in brandy for at least 2 hours. Cream butter and sugar; mix in egg and lemon peel.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in marinated fruits and nuts. Spoon into greased miniature muffin tins.
Place cherry on each. Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Drizzle each with brandy while warm, if desired.
Wrap in airtight container.
Store in cool place up to 2 months, adding more brandy each week.
Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices; place on greased 12-inch pizza pan; press together.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, then cool.
Cream together cream cheese, vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar for second layer.
Arrange the fruit in rings on the cream cheese mixture in order given, beginning at outside.
Mound blueberries in center.
Stir cornstarch, 1 cup sugar, water, salt, and orange and lemon juices together.
Bring to boil over medium heat and cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour cooled sauce over fruit, sealing edges.
Chill.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add applesauce and frozen raspberries; chill until set.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Spread refried beans in a large cake pan.
Mix 1/4 teaspoon taco seasoning in with the sour cream.
Spread on guacamole. Cover with chopped lettuce.
Spread on chopped tomatoes; then top with black olives and chopped green onions.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate and serve with chips and picante sauce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; add cut-up banana and stir in whipped cream.

title: one-pot brandy-applesauce spice cake
directions: Measure the flour in a 4-cup measuring cup and mix in the baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and allspice until thoroughly blended.
Toss in the raisins and set aside.
In a large saucepan, melt the butter.
Remove from heat and stir in the sugar, applesauce, eggs, vanilla and brandy.
With a whisk, mix in the dry ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch baking pan (square) and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes, until tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: hamburger nachos
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes to meat. Let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve over chips or as dip.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Beat everything together until creamy.
Put one wafer in each muffin cup.
Foil muffin liners work the best.
Fill 1/2 with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until set.
Top with filling when cold.
This will make about 20 cherry cheese tarts.

title: apricot-applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 cup Bundt pan or tube pan. Combine flour, allspice and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion, salt, pepper, salad pepper and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and chili powder.
Stir and add water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours with lid.
Thicken with flour and water.

title: peach frost frozen dessert
directions: Place peaches in blender with syrup and ground ginger.
Cover and blend until smooth. Add the lemon sherbet and ginger ale. Blend until smooth. Serve in large glasses with vanilla ice cream. Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In casserole, arrange broccoli and chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle cheese over contents, then top with bread crumbs.
(You can start with a layer of rice on the bottom and not use bread crumbs, if you wish.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except baking powder, eggs and milk.
Then add all other ingredients.
Pour into deep layer pan lined with shortening and heavy wax paper.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken livers with herbed rice
directions: Halfway through cooking rice, stir in chicken livers.
Cover and cook, stirring twice, until rice is cooked and livers are done.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Layer tomatoes, toast cubes and onions in greased casserole using 3/4 of the toast cubes.
Sprinkle the seasonings on the tomato layer.
Arrange remaining toast cubes over top.
Pour over all 1/4 cup margarine, melted.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute
onion
and
celery
in margarine.
Cook broccoli with onion
and celery until thawed, about 10 minutes. Combine all ingredients.
Pour	into casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine dressing, onion soup mix and apricot preserves; pour over chickens in shallow dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Baste several times.

title: chocolate sheet pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients and press into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees;
cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust and refrigerate. Spread chocolate pudding over cream cheese mixture and chill for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole (microwave)
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Layer in casserole with Tater Tots. Top with Tater Tots and onions.
Mix soups and pour over. Microwave 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies with cherries and toffee
directions: Sift the flour and baking soda and set aside.

title: unbaked peanut butter  bars
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and butterscotch chips together. Cool some then add marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Butter 11 x 16 inch pan.
Pat mixture into it.
Cool until firm, in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Pastel colored marshmallows may be used to give a party look.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach butter
directions: Simmer the peaches in the water until the skin is easy to remove.

Peel and pit the peaches, saving the cooking liquid. Puree the peaches (you will have about 8 cups) and place with the liquid (about 1/2 cup) and the sugar in a pot and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until thick, about 3 hours.
Taste and add optional liqueur or brandy and cook a few minutes more.
Add the ginger, if desired.
Remove from the heat and cool.
Place in a container in the refrigerator and keep refrigerated or freeze until ready to
use.
Makes 4 pints.

title: cheddar crisp
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into 2 logs on wax paper.
Chill at least 2 hours before baking or just freeze to cut and bake later.

title: mock condensed milk
directions: Place warm water in a bowl.
Add dry milk; mix well.
Add sugar; mix until smooth.
Bowl may be set in a pan of hot water to help dissolve sugar.

title: quick soup
directions: Cook hamburger until done.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut off tips of wings and cut wings in halves.
Place in a single layer in a baking pan.
Cover with soy sauce to about 1/2 inch.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Place a pat of butter on each. Bake in a slow oven, 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, turning at least once.
Serve as an appetizer, hot or cold.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice eggs, add onions, mustard, sugar, salad dressing and mix well.
Then add potatoes.
Refrigerate.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Blend cake mix with sugar, oil and nectar, adding eggs one at a time.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. While hot, mix juice of 2 lemons with 1 cup powdered sugar and pour on top of cake.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Place the popped corn in a large roaster.
Combine margarine (melt), sugar, syrup and salt together; boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda (will make it foamy).
Pour at once over popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring thoroughly with egg spatula every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir again and dump onto wax paper.
Break apart.
Let set for a few minutes. Store in airtight container.
Keeps a long time.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix taco sauce with water per package directions. Add to cooked hamburger and let simmer while you prepare the beans/veggies. Mix all ingredients together, except Doritos, in a big bowl. When ready to serve, open Doritos and crunch up in bag. Add to mixture, toss and enjoy. Each person can customize with hot sauce, sour cream, olives, hot peppers and cheese. Serves an army.

title: carrot, zucchini and romaine salad
directions: Tear romaine into bite-size pieces.
Trim zucchini.
Cut in half lengthwise and then into very thin slices.
Put romaine, zucchini, carrots, onions and parsley in a bowl.
Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Toss with other ingredients.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Boil noodles in kettle of salted water; meanwhile, beat butter until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and cream.
When well blended, beat in cheese, salt and plenty of black pepper.
Drain noodles well; toss with sauce, serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in top of double boiler. Add milk slowly. Cook in double boiler, stirring until thickened. Add slightly beaten egg yolks and cook 3 minutes longer. Remove from fire. Add peanut butter and vanilla. When cool, pour into baked crust. Cover with meringue or whipping cream.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Heat vinegar and sugar until dissolved. Then add celery seed, salt, pepper and gelatin.
Cool.
When cool add salad oil and pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate several hours prior to serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll 1/4 biscuits in sugar mixture (white sugar and cinnamon). Melt butter and mix with white and brown sugars. Put biscuits in Bundt pan. Pour sugar and butter mixture over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "wassail"(beverage)
directions: In
large
saucepan, heat cider and 1 cinnamon stick to boiling.
Reduce
heat,
cover
and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and stir in remaining ingredients (except cinnamon sticks) and simmer 5
minutes longer.	Serve in punch bowl.
Use cinnamon sticks
as individual stirrers.
Makes 16 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Fry bacon until well done.
Add onions, celery and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add veal, pork and liver.
Cook 1 hour on low flame.
Add soup and water; stir well and add green onions and parsley.
Season to taste.
Bake corn bread as directed on package.
Crumble and add to mixture.
Stir well and serve hot. Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; cool. Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard. Beat again. Add bread and stir.
Add cheese and sausage.
Pour in greased glass dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or brown around the edges.
Bake, uncovered.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown, drain and crumble sausage.
Sprinkle over bread cubes, then add shredded Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the a.m., mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over mixture and bake for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce, walnuts and apples.
Pour into Tupperware mold and refrigerate.

title: christmas cheesecake
directions: Combine gingersnaps, 1/3 cup almonds and cinnamon.
Add butter; blend well.
Press evenly into bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: buttermilk puffs
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk, oil and egg. Beat all ingredients until smooth.
A mixer is not necessary for this.
A fork will do.
Drop with teaspoon (too large puffs will not cook through) into hot fat (375°).
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Roll warm puffs in granulated or powdered sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients for dressing and refrigerate (can put in mayo jar).

title: after show pork roast
directions: Rub garlic salt and pepper on roast.
Bake at 350° or 2 to 3 hours or until done.
Can add potatoes and carrots around the roast for the last hour.

title: golden raisin truffles
directions: Melt chocolate with cream.
Add raisins.
Cover and refrigerate until set, about 4 hours.
Scoop into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: lemon bars
directions: Spread on baked crust.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes more.
Cool and sprinkle reserved powdered sugar on top.
Cut into bars.

title: shrimp rice casserole for two
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan over low direct heat.
Cook onion in butter until transparent, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in cream and Worcestershire sauce gradually.
Return to heat and cook sauce, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and shrimp.
Heat until warm, about 2 minutes.

title: chewy molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, ginger, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, combine vegetable oil, molasses and sugar; mix at speed 5 until thoroughly blended (about 2 minutes).
Add eggs; blend for 1 minute.
Reduce to speed 1.
Gradually add flour mixture; beat well (about 1 minute).
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixture until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Drain the fruit, reserving the juice. Place the fruit on top of the pie filling.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add other ingredients; put 1/2 mixture in a bowl and chill.
When set, spread 1 pint sour cream on top of Jell-O, then pour rest of Jell-O mixture on sour cream. Chill and serve.

title: sausage "n" taters
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Put bacon grease in a nonstick skillet.
When skillet and grease are hot, add potatoes.
Fry potatoes with cover on, stirring occasionally.
While potatoes are frying, cut the sausage into 1/8-inch slices.
Peel and dice the onion.
When potatoes are almost done, add the sausage and onion; continue frying until onion has turned clear and the sausage is heated through.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: escalloped corn with oysters
directions: Drain oysters; reserve liquid.
Grease shallow baking dish. Arrange 1/2 oysters and 1/2 drained corn in pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top, then another layer of oysters and corn.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix 3/4 of the oyster liquid, melted butter and cream and pour over the oysters and corn; chill.
Approximately 30 minutes before dinner, heat oven to 425°.
Top mixture with additional crumbs and bake 20 minutes or until bubbles and crumbs are browned.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Lightly brown nuts in small amount of oil.
Remove.
Stir-fry vegetables until tender-crisp.
Place all ingredients in pan and reheat.
Serve over rice.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water about 3 minutes until limp.
Drain.
Place about 1/4 cup mixture of rice, egg, milk, onion, salt, pepper and ground beef in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold in sides and roll ends over meat.
Place in slow cooker (crock-pot if desired).
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours.

title: chocolate meringue drops
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
With electric mixer beat egg whites until stiff peaks.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; add vanilla.
On low speed beat in cocoa; fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto baking sheets.
Bake 1 hour; shut oven off.
Let stand in oven 2 hours. Makes 40 cookies; 23 calories, 19 fat, 0 cholesterol.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients carefully but thoroughly.
Add cream slowly and vinegar, very slowly.
Slow mixing is to prevent curdling.
Makes 1 1/2 pints and keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk.
Heat per directions.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 of pudding on crackers.
Add another layer of crackers, then remaining 1/2 of pudding and end layering with more crackers. Frost with can of chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes, in large bowl.
Shape into a loaf; place in crockpot.
Put potatoes at the sides of the loaf. (If potatoes are peeled, wrap in foil to keep from darkening.)
Cover and cook on low 8-10 hours (High 4-5 hours).

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix and refrigerate 2 hours.
Shape into walnut-sized balls. Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Make paste with cocoa and water and add to mixture.
Mix together buttermilk and soda and add alternately with flour and salt.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; pour into blender.
Add can of cranberries.
Blend for 1 minute.
Add nuts; blend for a few seconds more.
Pour half into 8-inch square pan.
Set overnight or until feels firm.
Spread sour cream over top.
Pour the rest of mixture over sour cream.
Set again.

title: raspberry champagne punch
directions: Puree raspberries.
Combine berries, lemon juice, sugar and wine in punch bowl.
Stir well.
Just before serving, scoop in sherbet.
Add champagne.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix salt, sugar, vinegar, oil, and water.
Pour over vegetables.
Let marinate overnight.
Drain off liquid and serve.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add 1 3/4 cups Velveeta cheese, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese, sour cream and milk.
Reduce heat.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Add chicken.
Place 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla and roll up.
Place seam-side down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining mixture and 1/4 cup Velveeta Mexican cheese and 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with tomatoes or black olives.

title: picante sauce
directions: Flour stew meat and brown in skillet.
Add onion, mango and water to cover.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: beef or smoked sausage and green beans
directions: Boil (cook) meat until almost done (1 hour or so) in a pan big enough to hold both meat and beans.
Add bouillon, onion and garlic.
Add beans.
Simmer while covered until beans are done. Add salt, if desired.

title: onion dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.

title: mexican pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan.
Mix Bisquick, cornmeal and 1/2 cup water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Pat in pan with floured hands, forming 1/2-inch rim.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown.
Stir in seasoning mix and 3/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered until thickened 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread beans over crust.
Top with beef and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serve with topping and taco sauce.

title: cocoa fudge frosting(microwave)
directions: Microwave butter until melted, about 1 minute.
Stir in cocoa until smooth.
Microwave on High until mixture boils, 1/2 to 1 minute.
Add milk and sugar.
Blend in vanilla.
Spread while warm.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly in a bowl.
Put a little cooking oil on your hands and shape it into a ball.
Serve with crackers.
Very colorful and tasty.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix tomatoes, sugar and bread that has been torn into smaller sizes.
Put in pie dish or any dish that will hold this.
Put dots of butter on top.
Sprinkle black pepper on top.
Put in 350° oven to bake until brown on top.

title: cake-like oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in a pan; simmer over medium heat until raisins are plump, about 15 minutes.
Drain, saving liquid. Add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.
