Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; stir in liquid and raisins.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: sweet bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water; set aside.
Heat until warm the milk and 2 1/2 cups of water (5 cups of liquid). Add milk and water to shortening, sugar, salt and beaten eggs. Measure and add to liquid the flour 3 cups at a time.
Grease hands; knead well.
Let rise for 2 hours or until doubled in bulk. Knead again and put dough in greased pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 pan loaves.

title: super deluxe au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix thawed potatoes, melted butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Use a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soups and vegetables.
Melt 2 sticks of butter and mix with this and remaining ingredients (except chicken).
Place chicken in baking dish and pour mixture over chicken.
Bake in 450° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yogurt topped vegetable pie
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Saute vegetables just until tender. Stir in spices.
Remove from heat and toss with flour and wine. Puree eggs and cottage cheese in blender.
Add to sauteed vegetables.
Mix well.
Spread into pastry lined pie pan.
Stir yogurt and sour cream until creamy.
Spread on top of vegetable filling.
Wash, trim and slice mushrooms.
Saute lightly in butter and arrange gently on top of yogurt layer.
Dust with paprika. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Boil frozen hash browns in unsalted water until almost tender. Melt cheese and mix with mayonnaise.
Drain potatoes and stir in cheese mixture.
Put into well-greased dish and top with Bac*Os. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 or 50 minutes (until it begins to bubble in center).

title: praline candy
directions: Cook until it forms a firm ball in water.
Quickly drop on waxed paper.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling and pineapple on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Put coconut, nuts and dry cake mix in bowl and stir.
Put on top of filling and pineapple.
Cut butter into thin slices and place close together on top of mixture.
Cover entire top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels; pat dry.
Remove stems and finely chop; set aside.
Brush caps with melted butter.
Saute stems, celery, onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add wine and Worcestershire; simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in breadcrumbs.
Spoon mixture by tablespoon into caps.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese potato bread
directions: In
large
bowl,
combine
yeast
from foil packet with flour mixture, potato flakes, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt. Stir in hot
tap
water and egg until flour is moistened;
add Cheddar cheese.
Stir
until
well
mixed
(batter
will
be sticky). Cover;
let
rise
on
wire rack over bowl or pan to which boiling water
has been added until light and doubled in size, 30
to
45 minutes.
Generously
grease 10-inch tube or 9-inch round
cake pan.
Stir
down dough; spread in prepared pan.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, about 30
to 45 minutes.
Heat oven at 375°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes
or
until golden
brown.
Immediately remove from pan.

title: choc-o-date dessert
directions: Reserve 1/4
cup
cookie crumbs.
Spread remainder in a 10 x 6 1/2-inch pan.
In a saucepan, combine dates, water and salt; bring to
a boil and simmer for 3 minutes.	Remove from heat; add marshmallows
and
stir until melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in nuts and spread over crumbs in pan.
Whip cream and
vanilla. Swirl
over
dates.
Sprinkle
with
reserved crumbs.
Top
with walnut
halves.
Chill
overnight,	cut in squares and serve.

title: ham 'n' cheese pinwheels
directions: Beat softened cream cheese, horseradish and chives.
Spread each meat slice with about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Top with cheese slice and spread with another tablespoon cheese mixture. Roll-up.
Chill.
Slice each roll into 5 pieces.
Serve with toothpicks in each slice.
These can be frozen for use later.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Roll into loaf and refrigerate.
Cut into desired size and bake at 350° from 7 to 8 minutes. Check your oven heat as all ovens differ.

title: low-fat banana smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients together for quick nutritious snack or low-fat breakfast.
Only 220 calories and 1 gram fat.

title: prize-winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; pack into ungreased pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: orange slush
directions: Combine 3 cups water and sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes and let cool.
Then add frozen orange juice concentrate, 1 can water, crushed pineapple juice, chopped bananas and drained cherries. Freeze to slush.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Boil syrup, sugar, butter and salt to heavy syrup stage. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Mix in milk thoroughly. Serve over ice cream, brownies, etc.

title: gingerbread christmas cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch pans.
Mix all ingredients except shredded coconut and chopped walnuts.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Mix at medium speed for 4 minutes. Add coconut and walnuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake immediately for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Make up the instant mashed potatoes.
Add the remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole; top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add vegetable soup, celery and tomato juice.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Put mashed potatoes on top and cheese on top of the potatoes.
Bake in moderate oven until cheese melts.

title: hot dog soup
directions: Melt butter; saute sliced onion rings.
Add crushed tomatoes, water, sugar, cubes, spices and Worcestershire sauce.
Add rice. When rice is almost cooked, add sliced hot dogs.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon peel.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add alternately the milk and flour to creamed mixture.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until loaf springs back when lightly touched.
Pierce top of hot loaf with tines of fork.
Pour Lemon Syrup over cake.
Let stand 10 minutes before turning out of pan. Chill.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown orzo until golden in butter, stirring frequently, for about 5 minutes.
Add rice and chicken broth.
Cover pilaf; simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let rest before serving.
To make chicken broth, dissolve 2 chicken bouillon cubes in 2 cups water.

title: melba's delight
directions: Combine and mix well the flour, margarine and chopped nuts. Pat into bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and dessert topping.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pistachio pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
When puddings have set, mix together gently and spread on top of cheese layer.
Chill.
Garnish with additions, whipped topping, if desired.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: applesauce cobbler
directions: Spread applesauce in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Top with brown sugar and pecans.
Cover with margarine (sliced).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: the best beefy bake beans around
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash cooked sweet potatoes.
Mix in eggs.
Add 1/4 of the brown sugar and 1/4 of the butter.
Add salt and cinnamon.
Mix in orange juice.
Spread out in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Put pecans on top.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and butter over top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: seafood sausage kabobs
directions: Make Marinade:
Whisk oil, lemon juice, garlic, cumin, tarragon, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add shrimp; toss to coat. Refrigerate, covered, turning shrimp occasionally (at least 3 hours).
Drain shrimp, reserving marinade.
Thread metal skewers alternately with zucchini, shrimp and sausage.
Place skewers on barbecue; brush kabobs with marinade.
Barbecue about 6 minutes on each side, basting frequently with marinade.
Makes 8 to 10 kabobs.

title: miz malv's sausage soup
directions: God chooses the main ingredient. . . parents.
Just add the following ingredients.
Do not simmer, stew or boil.
This could cause your recipe to ruin.

title: new jersey glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add picante sauce for a spicier recipe.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in hot water in a large bowl.
Fold in all at once the thawed strawberries (with juice), drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish or mold. Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 12.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saute garlic, onions and green peppers in 3 tablespoons water. Add
next
ingredients.
Fold
in
cheese.
Bake in sprayed casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry glazed chicken
directions: Heat all ingredients except chicken, until bubbly and smooth. Pour over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine oil and 1 cup sugar in a bowl.
Add egg and beat.
Stir in molasses and vanilla, then dry ingredients. Roll into about 1-inch balls and dip into remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Bake about 10 minutes or until done but not too dark.
Has butter flavor after stored a few days.

title: melted moments cookies
directions: Drop from teaspoon onto rolled oat base.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chitterlings
directions: Clean chitterlings thoroughly, removing as much of the fat as possible.
Place the chitterlings in a pot and add cold water, a little lemon juice and salt.
Let stand for awhile.
Change water, adding more lemon juice and salt as necessary.
Rinse chitterlings thoroughly and put them back in the pot.
Add cold water to cover, juice and the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until chitterlings are thoroughly tender, about 4 hours. Serve hot with vinegar and hot sauce on the side.

title: eclair cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place the water in a medium-sized saucepan.
Heat until moderately hot.
Reduce heat to low.
Add the butter and melt.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter.
Bring to a boil.
(If too thick, add more water.)
Cover and simmer, stirring often. Add butter.
Remove from heat and stir.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: breakfast hot pockets
directions: Fry/scramble sausage in a large skillet until it is well done.
Drain grease from sausage.
Mix drained sausage and cream cheese in a large bowl with a large spoon until the cheese is "melted" and well blended with the sausage.
Preheat oven to 375°. Open crescent roll can carefully, do not allow dough to separate. Lay dough on a large cookie sheet, side by side.
If there are any cracks use your fingers to "mush" dough together.
Spoon half the sausage/cheese mixture down center of crescent rolls.
Fold both of the sides of each crescent roll to the center, overlapping at center point making it look like a large hot pocket.
Bake for 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into number of servings you need after removing from oven.
Eat and enjoy!

title: pasta fagoli
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add chicken broth, tomato sauce, beans (with juice), salt, pepper, basil and parsley.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups of ditalini to broth.
Bring to a slow boil until macaroni is al dente.
Serve with grated Romano cheese and Italian bread.
Add hot pepper flakes, if desired.

title: chocolate midnight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Generously grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. Mix cake mix, water, mayonnaise, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl. Beat slow for 1 minute, then fast for 2 minutes. Equally divide the cake mix between the 2 pans. Bake for 28 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely before frosting.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk. In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients, but save enough flour to coat fruit.
Add the dry ingredients then add all the fruit.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake in loaf or tube pans at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Place chicken breasts in well buttered shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix soup, onion and cheese spread together and heat until cheese melts.
Combine with hominy and place in a casserole dish. Top with corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green beans a la gertis
directions: Cook green string beans in small amount of hot water.
Add cream of onions, water chestnuts and salt.
Serve hot.

title: corn muffins(makes 6 to 12 servings)
directions: In medium bowl, stir together corn bread mix and flour. Chop onion and pepper into small squares on a cutting board. Mix onion and pepper with vegetable oil and stir into flour. Break eggs in a small bowl and beat. Pour into dough and mix well. Add enough buttermilk to make a consistency similar to cake dough. Pour batter into muffin pan molds. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven. While hot, brush each top with liquid butter.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream oil, eggs and sugar Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, plus a 9-inch square pan, that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix beef, rice, 1/2 can of soup, egg, water and salt.
Form the mixture into meatballs.
Arrange them in a circle in microwave-safe pan and cover with wax paper.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes on High.
Top with remaining soup.

title: best in the west beans
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add combined sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses and seasoning.
Mix well.
Add to drained beans.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: brownies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter with sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Add vanilla.
Melt remaining butter with chocolate; cool and beat into first mixture.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into small squares.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt stick of margarine.
Add both cans of undiluted soup. Add the rice to soup mixture and pour into large baking dish. Place salted chicken pieces over rice mixture.
Bake covered for 2 1/2 or 3 hours at 300°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: neiman-marcus chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and oatmeal, then add remaining ingredients. Roll into balls; place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes approximately 115 cookies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Slice the potatoes into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish and cover with green beans.
Cover beans with the entire can of mushroom soup and top with the onions (dilute soup a little bit). Sprinkle with paprika and microwave for 7 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1 angel food cake.
Put in bottom of punch bowl.
Add crushed pineapple.
Add 1 1/2 cans cherry pie filling.
Add 1 vanilla pudding.
Layer again with remaining ingredients.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with fruit.
Chill.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Simmer together in 9-inch skillet brown sugar and butter.
Arrange pineapple slices on top of butter and sugar mixture.
Place one cherry in center of each slice; pour batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Turn out at once.

title: chocolate for easter eggs
directions: Add a
little
paraffin
in double boiler.
Melt on low heat, add
Hershey bar and chocolate chips.
Keep on low.
Now take shaped eggs
and
an open spoon or server.
Dip in to the coating, then place on wax paper on a cookie sheet.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add tea bags.
Cook 15 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add orange juice, lemonade and whiskey.
Place container in freezer for 24 hours.
Spoon slush in glass.
Add 7-Up.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Dip the pork chops in beaten eggs and then into bread crumbs. Brown the chops on top of the stove.
Add water.
Cover and bake in the oven until tender.

title: ginger dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: elsie dodge's molasses cookies
directions: Put alum and soda in cup of hot water.
Use flour enough for soft dough.
Roll out and cut with cutter.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes and jalapeno peppers.
Add other ingredients. Stir.
Chill before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon strips. Pour in baking dish & place bacon strips on top. Bake about 1 hour at 350 degrees. (Check in about 45 minutes.) This is a recipe that you try and adapt to your own taste.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over the fruit layers (don't mix). Dot top with margarine.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
(If desired, sprinkle coconut over mixture a few minutes before removing from oven.)
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt the ingredients.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet. Refrigerate for about 1/2 hour.

title: christmas dip
directions: Place ingredients in blender container.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with raw vegetables or corn chips.
Garnish platter with cherry tomatoes and parsley sprigs.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown beef in skillet and add to ingredients.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for one hour (covered).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl cream butter with sugars until light.
Add eggs; mix well.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine flour, spices, salt and soda.
Add to sugar mixture and stir well.
Stir in applesauce, chocolate chips, raisins, coconut and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: carrot salad
directions: Let carrots set overnight in mixture of remaining ingredients (mixture does not have to be cooked); dissolve sugar in vinegar, oil and tomato soup and add other ingredients.
Use Pyrex bowl. Serves about 20.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt with pastry blender until well blended.
Add milk; stir until ball of dough cleans sides of bowl.
Divide into 3 equal pieces.
Roll out on floured surface. Will make three 8-inch or two 9-inch pie shells.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Add water to soup and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and blend in cheese.
Stir until melted.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add spaghetti and turkey.
Serve on a hot platter sprinkled with parsley.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix pancake mix and ginger ale together until you get a thick mixture.
Dip onion ring into mixture and fry in hot oil until brown.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon in saucepan.
Add bananas and banana liqueur.
Let cook until thoroughly heated. Flame with brandy; serve over ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: veggi pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls in jelly roll pan (or pizza pan) and press seams together. Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: moist apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix 3 cups flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add this to mixture.
Cut and dice apples, add nuts (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: baked fudge
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and butter and beat well again. Sift cocoa and flour together. Add pecans. Fold into sugar, butter and egg mixture. Add vanilla. Pour in 9 x 12 x 3-inch dish or pan. Set pan in a pan of hot water (enough to come 1/2 to 1-inch up on sides of pan). Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Fudge will have the consistency of firm custard and will be crusty on top. Serve warm with a dollop of whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Grind up chicken, carrots and peas.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with sauce (cream of mushroom or tomato).

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in pan.
Cook over low heat until thick and smooth.
Put in bowl and cool.
Cream oleo and shortening for 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Add sugar gradually and beat for 4 minutes.
Add flour paste and beat 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: ritz torte
directions: Combine crackers, nuts, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9-inch round cake pan. Top each pieces with berries and whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cook and stir 4 cups zucchini, thinly
sliced with 1 cup chopped onion in 1/4 cup margarine or butter.
Combine salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano and
add
mixture
to
zucchini
and
onion.
Combine
eggs and cheese.
Stir
into zucchini, onion mixture.
Separate 8 ounces crescent dinner rolls, place them in ungreased 10-inch pie pan. Press
the crescent rolls together to form crust.
Spread crust with
mustard;
add
vegetable mixture.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Beat the egg whites, sugar and dash of salt until stiff.
Mix the pecans and walnuts.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Chop or slice vegetables and mix with cool macaroni.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Reserve juice from pineapple.
Slice bananas and mix with drained fruit.
Cook pie filling using pineapple juice instead of milk.
Let cool and pour over fruit.

title: chicken casserole(from southern cooking)
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with Swiss cheese.
Thin soup with water or wine; mix until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with butter and sprinkle over top.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar icing
directions: Mix all together well and use for decorating cookies, etc.

title: kruschiki(bow ties)
directions: Combine in 3 steps, the first 2, then the next 4, then the last 2.
Chill until firm. Fry in shortening until golden 1/2 to 1 minute.
Cut with slit in middle.
Pull one end through to form bow tie.
Roll in powdered sugar after frying.

title: danish sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Cream butter, sugar and egg, then add remainder of ingredients.
Cool in refrigerator.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts; place on cookie sheet and mash with fork. Bake 12 minutes, or until lightly browned, in 375° oven.

title: olive tarts
directions: Mix cheese and butter well.
Stir in all other ingredients, except olives.
Take a small ball of dough and flatten it with your hands.
Wrap it around the olive, making a ball of dough with olive inside.
Freeze until ready to use.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: meat rub seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes enough seasoning for 10 pounds meat.
Rub on meat.
Place in refrigerator overnight before barbecuing.

title: beef palla
directions: Simmer ingredients together for approximately 45 minutes.
Cut up 1 pound of beef into bite-size pieces and add together.

title: laprairie's yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water and add remaining ingredients. Add plain flour to mixture until dough is stiff. Let rise until double in bulk. Knead thoroughly. Form into balls and let rise. Bake at 375°.

title: carrot soup
directions: Slice carrots (in Cuisinart, if available).
Cover with water; simmer for 40 minutes, but don't boil.
Drain.
Dice or shred onions (in Cuisinart).
Saute in butter or margarine in large pot. Add chicken stock and carrots.
Simmer for 40 minutes.
Puree in Cuisinart (or blender).
Add 1 1/4 cups orange juice.
Serve hot or cold with dollop of yogurt and parsley.
Serves 4.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in pineapple and sugar. Let cool 45 minutes in refrigerator.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 inch square dish.

title: p.t.a.  punch
directions: Dissolve jello into 5 cups of boiling water.
Boil sugar with 4 cups of water for 1 minute.
Add pineapple juice and lemonade to make a concentrate.

title: special k fruit cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend margarine and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and spoon into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Combine undiluted soup, 1/2 cup cheese, milk, mayonnaise, eggs and red pepper.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over broccoli.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: 3-b casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Mix beef, onion, beans, barbecue sauce and brown sugar together.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish sprayed with Pam.
Shred Cheddar cheese on top.
Cut biscuits in half and lay on top.
Bake for 22 to 27 minutes at 375°.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: In large bowl or pitcher blend lemon, cranberry and pineapple juice with sugar. Stir until dissolved and add ginger ale.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: While squash and onions are cooking, brown sausage and drain. Mash squash/onions and mix with sausage, cottage cheese and stuffing mix.
Put in casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Bake 350° about 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Servings 6 to 8.

title: waldorf grape salad
directions: Gently toss together grapes, apples, celery and walnuts.
Thin mayonnaise with milk; stir in lemon juice.
Add to grape mixture and toss.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cranberry whiskey coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, whiskey, oil, milk and eggs together on low speed.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes more on high speed.
Fold in nuts, coconut and berries.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when almost cold.

title: pear honey
directions: Grind fruit with small plate in grinder. Add pectin. Place in pan and bring to boil, boil for 1 minute, then add sugar. Bring to a rolling boil, (3 minutes). Pour into sterilized pint or 1/2 pint jars, seal.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Heat together the first 5 ingredients until thickened, then pour over cheese and pimento.
Mix together after cheese is slightly softened.

title: frances sonitzky's cocoa fudge brownies
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa and sugar together into a mixing bowl.
Add oil and milk and beat at a medium speed until smooth.
Fold the egg whites and nuts into the batter and pour it into a greased 9-inch square Pyrex cake pan.
Bake the brownies in a preheated slow oven (325°) for 30 minutes or until firm to the touch.
Cut the brownies into 4-inch squares while warm but not hot.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together until creamy.
Add sugar gradually until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon extract.
Blend in flour with spoon; fold in 7-Up.
Bake in well-greased tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: curried sweet potato strips
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 14 thin wedges.
Place in a large heavy-duty zip top bag.
Add oil, apple juice and curry powder to bag.
Seal bag and shake until potato wedges are well coated.

Remove potato wedges from bag and place in a single layer on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until crisp and lightly browned, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil about 5 minutes each side.
Add cranberry sauce which has been chopped into small pieces.
Add dressing.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with fluffy rice and put sauce over rice.
Delicious!
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Bake 1 hour at 325° for 1 hour in greased angel food cake pan.
Cool in pan for approximately 20 minutes.
Invert on cake plate.

title: baked strawberries
directions: Put strawberries, washed, hulled and halved, in a buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle berries with sugar, lemon juice and water.
Remove crust from four 1/2-inch slices of day old bread (white) and cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Cover berries with cubes and sprinkle with brown sugar and lemon rind.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bread cubes are slightly brown.
Serve warm with sweetened whipped cream flavored with Kirsch.
Serves 4.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill; add ginger ale just before serving.
I have used this recipe many times and always get compliments.
Makes 25 servings.

title: crab artichoke casserole
directions: Arrange artichoke hearts in a buttered shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top evenly with crab.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart pan over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and cook, stirring often, until mushrooms are soft and liquid has evaporated.
Blend in flour and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add milk and broth, stirring constantly.
Return to heat; cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and sherry. Pour sauce over crab mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water; stir in cold water.
Pour into a 6-cup mold.
Chill until set, but not firm.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Add the molasses, well beaten eggs, milk, melted butter and ginger or orange rind, in order, to the grated sweet potatoes. Turn into a well-greased baking pan and bake for about 45 minutes in a 350° oven, sprinkling brown sugar and cinnamon over the top at the end of first 25 minutes.

title: skillet burger
directions: Crumble hamburger and add chopped celery and onion while cooking.
Cook until done.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: new york pastry crust
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, lemon rind and vanilla in a bowl.
Add the egg yolk and butter and blend until the mixture forms a ball.
Put into a plastic bag or wrap in wax paper; chill for about 1 hour.
Divide the dough into quarters.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Separate the bottom from the sides.
Roll 1/4 of the dough directly on the bottom of the pan.
Trim the edges.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: noches
directions: Cut thin slice of cheese to cover each corn chip.
Add sliver of jalapeno pepper.
Place under broiler just until cheese melts. Serve warm.

title: bombay chicken salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and curry powder. Toss gently with remaining ingredients, except almonds, peaches, fruit juice and lettuce. Chill several hours before serving.
Dip peaches in fruit juice to prevent turning brown.
Mound chicken salad on lettuce leaves and surround with drained peach slices.
Top with almonds.
Serves 8 tol 10.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix strawberries with 1/4 cup sugar and let stand for 30 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center and add the strawberries and eggs.
Then add the oil and the nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour the batter into 2 greased standard size loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the bread tests done.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and slice into 3/4-inch slices.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomato slices into flour mixture.
Heat margarine in a 10-inch skillet until melted.
Add tomato slices; cook, turning once, until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Put in saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over meat balls.
Bake in oven about 1 hour.

title: confetti waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir for 3 minutes.
Stir in cold water and lemon juice.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Stir in mayonnaise with wire whisk.
Stir in apple, celery and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Let set for at least 4 hours.
Serves 10 nicely.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: You will need 4 (1 pound) clean coffee cans.

title: fresh fruit trifle
directions: In medium bowl, combine milk, yogurt and orange peel; blend well.
Beat until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
In large trifle bowl, layer half the cake pieces, 1/3 of the fruit and 1/2 the pudding.
Repeat layers.
Arrange remaining fruit on top. Cover and refrigerate 2 to 6 hours before serving.
Calories 130, fat 1 g.

title: lemon jello fruit salad
directions: In saucepan, mix juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Cook until thick.
Let cool completely.
Mix Jell-O, boiling water and 7-Up; let partially set while in bowl.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into Pyrex dish or mold.
To the sugar mixture, add Cool Whip, then pour over Jell-O mixture.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese or chopped pecans.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
(Can be used as salad or dessert.)
Serves 12 to 14.

title: artichokes and chicken
directions: Fry chicken cutlets dipped in eggs and bread crumbs until golden.
Cut artichokes in half and pour 1 can artichokes juice in pan.
Put chicken and artichokes and 1/4 bottle of salad dressing in pan and mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with rice and enjoy.

title: southern barbecued pork spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except ribs in a saucepan and boil for five minutes.
Cool; place ribs in a shallow baking dish and pour marinade over all.
Marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in the fridge.
Drain, reserving remaining marinade. Place ribs (rib end down) on grill 6 to 8 inches over grey-white coals.
Grill 45 minutes.
Baste.
Grill another 15 minutes, basting often with marinade.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup wafers.
Melt about 1/2 cup butter.
Add to remaining wafers and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Have remaining butter and eggs at room temperature.
Cream with the sugar, adding eggs one a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Spread over wafers.
Spread pineapple over creamed mixture. Spread Cool Whip over the pineapple.
Sprinkle reserved wafers and pecans on top. Chill overnight. Serves 18 to 20.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and eggs; add dry ingredients.
Dip blueberries into 1 cup of flour and fold into mixture.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin pie ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ice cream.
When all ingredients are mixed, fold in ice cream.
Refreeze.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes, then add boiling water.
Cool.
Blend together mayonnaise, lemon juice, celery, olives and salt; add tuna and gelatin.
Pour into a mold and chill until firm.
Good served on salad greens or with crackers.

title: sherry's carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients as you continue to mix by hand or electric mixer. Bake at 350°.
Time varies, depending on type of pan used.
Two round or square cake pans would take approximately 40 to 50 minutes.
Check frequently so as not to scorch.

title: one bowl apple kuchen
directions: Break eggs over apples.
Add sugar and oil; mix with a fork. Then add all the dry ingredients and mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Do not open oven until done.
When cool, drizzle a thin powdered sugar frosting on top.

title: dill dip (low-fat)
directions: Blend all together.
Store for at least 1/2 day for flavors to blend.
Use with fresh vegetables or chips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients; mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and combine with chicken mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with potato chips and bake at 350° until hot.

title: marinade for pork chops
directions: Place marinade in Ziploc bag with pork chops overnight.
Turn occasionally.
Grill or broil pork chops.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Sift dry ingredients 3 times and add alternately with sour cream to first mixture, beating until smooth. Add flavoring.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan lined on the bottom with waxed paper.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/3 hours or until done.
Let stand in pan on rack for about 5 minutes. Turn out and peel off paper. Cool. Frost with confectioners sugar glaze, allowing to run down sides.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix all together, then roll out the dough about 1/4-inch thick and cut with cookie cutters.
Nice if you can get a bone-shaped one.
Place on cookie sheets and brush with a mixture of one beaten egg plus some milk.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Cut chicken into 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Dip in butter.
Coat with cracker mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh rhubarb pie(custard)
directions: Put rhubarb, sugar, flour, salt and egg in a 9-inch pie shell. Bake 20 minutes at 450° (preheat oven).
Remove from oven and add 1/4 cup cream over the hot rhubarb pie.
Bake 15 minutes longer at 350° or until done.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread, as given, in order in long baking dish.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornmeal, flour and salt.
Mix and stir in margarine.
Add eggs and pineapple and beat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, cocoa, baking soda and sugar into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in ingredients:
first, 2 teaspoons vinegar; second, 2 teaspoons vanilla extract; third, 10 tablespoons oil.
Over whole thing, pour 2 cups water.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix everything but peanut butter together.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Constantly stir for five minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and 1 tsp vanilla.
Drop on to wax paper to cool.

title: fruit cake
directions: Use 1/2 cup flour to coat raisins, cherries and pecans.
You can add some cooked figs also if desired.
Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Turn oven to 300°.
Cream sugar and margarine good.
Add flavorings and eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing well.
Then take spatula and fold in raisins, cherries and pecans that have been coated in flour.
Bake in oven at 300° for 2 hours.
(Place pecan halves around on mixture before placing pan in oven.)
Cool cake 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and roll into balls.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on a buttered cookie sheet and cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, salt, dark corn syrup, vanilla and butter.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange nut cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar, add eggs one at a time. Add flour, sugar, salt, buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend for 30 seconds with mixer at low speed, scraping side of bowl constantly, switch to high speed and beat for 3 minutes.
Add raisins, nuts and peel, stirring with a spoon.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 inch pans.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or a wooden pick comes out clean.
Remove from oven and let set a few minutes, then turn out on racks to cool.
When thoroughly cool, frost with orange buttercream frosting.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add green chilies, 1 1/2 cups cheese and sausage.
Mix well.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
May need 10 to 15 minutes more.
Toothpick test will be clean when done.

title: festive chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Put into well greased 9x12 baking dish and refrigerate over night.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking and cover top of casserole with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for one hour uncovered at 375°. Let stand 15-20 minutes before cutting into serving squares.
Makes 12 delicious servings.
* Suggested variation:
Substitute 4 c. cooked cubed ham for the chicken, use 2 cans cream of celery soup in place of the mushroom soup, and 2 c. of milk instead of 1 c. chicken broth & 1 c. of milk.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Cream sugar
and
Crisco
together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add
cup
flour and 1/2 cup milk alternately, ending with flour.
Add flavorings last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease rectangular (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch) baking dish. Cook beef and onion over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until beef is brown. Drain beef. Stir in dry gravy mix, water and mushrooms. Cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream. Spoon mixture into baking dish.

title: red salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given and spread the Miracle Whip on top.
Cover bowl, store in refrigerator overnight.
Stir one hour before serving.

title: pineapple-strawberry cheesecake
directions: Combine bread crumbs, ground walnuts, cinnamon and 3 teaspoons of the margarine in a medium-size bowl.
Lightly grease bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan with the remaining 1 teaspoon margarine.
Press crumb mixture on bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of spring-form pan.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: microwave quick tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted boiling water; drain.
Place in microwave casserole dish.
Add tuna, salt and both soups. Microwave 5 minutes.
Add potato chips, rotate dish and cook 4 more minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese; cook 1 minute.
Let stand 2 minutes and serve.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients and then pour over cereal.
When cereal is well covered, shake in powdered sugar.
Store in an airtight container.

title: raspberry applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce until bubbles.
Add Jell-O; stir and heat until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add 7-Up and orange juice. Refrigerate until set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: dublin potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar and mustard.
Cook potatoes in salted water. Drain and cube.
While potatoes are still warm, drizzle with vinegar mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Chill.

title: ham or pepperoni cups
directions: Chop
pepperoni
or ham.
Mix all ingredients together. Grease tins.
Fill halfway and bake at 350° until brown, 20 to 30 minutes.
Use mini tins.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: In a large bowl, let egg whites warm to room temperature, about 1 hour.
Cook broccoli in boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Combine broccoli, skim milk and nutmeg in blender.
Blend, at high speed, to make a smooth puree (you should have 2 1/3 cups).
Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 1-quart souffle dish with nonfat cooking spray.
In a medium saucepan, combine liquid Butter Buds with flour and broccoli puree.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
In a small bowl, beat some of the hot mixture into the Egg Beaters; pour back into rest of the mixture.
Set aside.
At high speed, beat egg whites with 1/2 teaspoon salt until stiff peaks form.
With a rubber spatula, fold broccoli mixture into egg whites until just combined.
Turn into a prepared souffle dish.
Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Serve at once with a nonfat cheese or Hollandaise sauce.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Melt chocolate and cool.
Add egg, vanilla and milk to butter mix.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Chill.
Roll dough into marble sized balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until tops are cracked.
Remove. While hot, roll in 10x sugar.
Cool on wire racks.
Roll again in 10x sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, celery, green pepper, onion, salt, pepper and paprika; set aside.
Grease casserole; cover bottom with chicken. Pour some of the soup mixture over the chicken.
Repeat, chicken and cover with soup mixture.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: dressing for cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together with the salad.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large punch bowl.
If ingredients are not chilled, you can use ice cubes.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat to boiling (except chicken). Line a large, shallow pan with foil and grease, leaving foil so that it will fold over top of chicken.
Place chicken on foil. Pour ingredients over chicken.
Seal foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350°.
Cool 1 hour.
Do not open foil while cooking.

title: brandy butter(sauce)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until smooth.
Gradually stir in the brandy and add the nutmeg.
Beat thoroughly and transfer to a dish or small pot.
Cover and allow to harden before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: drop fudge icing
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until a soft ball can be rolled between fingers.
Add vanilla and large piece of butter.
Set in cool place without stirring until perfectly cold.
Beat until stiff and drop on oil paper.
Transfer to cake.

title: dottie's praline cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and cook for 3 minutes. Add and melt the 20 marshmallows.
Add graham crackers and nuts. Drop on wax paper.

title: old-fashioned icing
directions: Bring Carnation and sugar to a boil and add oleo; sit off fire and add egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Return to stove and cook until thick.
Remove from stove and add coconut and nuts.

title: whoppie pies
directions: Add dry ingredients, then milk and water. Stir and drop by teaspoon or tablespoon on cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb strawberry crunch
directions: Mix together 1 c. white sugar and 3 Tbsp. flour.
Add rhubarb and strawberries.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix together brown sugar, 1 1/2 c. flour, butter and oats until crumbly. Crumble on top of rhubarb and strawberry mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Heat shortening in heavy saucepan or skillet.
Add onions and cook until brown.
Add beef, salt, chili powder, paprika and black pepper and cook until done but not brown.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over mixture and cook slow.
Add tomato sauce and flour. Cover and cook about 30 minutes over low heat.

title: coconut eggnog
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Dust with cinnamon.

title: potluck
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water until done and drain.
Brown beef and onions.
Add tomato sauce and cook gently for 5 minutes. Combine all ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle a little cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves six.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Measure Southern Comfort into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and lemonade.
Scoop sherbet on top.
Makes half a punch bowl.

title: tamale ring
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Pour into a well-greased ring mold (8 inches in diameter and 2 inches deep).
Set in pan of hot water; bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When baked, unmold on platter; decorate with watercress.
Fill center with creamed chicken; sprinkle with fine chopped parsley.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil 6 cups squash and 1/2 cup onion for 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly (be sure to squeeze out all the liquid).
Fold soup with sour cream.
Melt margarine and stir in the bag of stuffing mix.
Combine squash/onion mix with the sour cream and soup. Place half the stuffing on bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Pour squash mixture on top, then top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling through.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add lard and buttermilk and beat for 2 minutes, then add eggs and beat for 1 minute.
Pour batter into 1 oblong 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chesapeake bay crab cakes
directions: Break bread and moisten with milk.
Add all other ingredients. Make into cakes.
Fry quickly until browned.

title: spicy percolator punch
directions: Place cranberry juice, pineapple juice, water and brown sugar in percolator.
Place cinnamon, cloves and allspice in basket. Perk as for coffee.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: In crock-pot stir together the potatoes and onion. Stir in the bacon.

title: mushroom dip
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; drain liquid.
Add flour; stir to coat mushrooms well.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in sour cream; season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spread in 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve on crackers.
May prepare 1 day ahead.

title: harvest bread
directions: Use electric mixer and beat well the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add by hand (blending) potatoes, orange juice and all dry ingredients sifted together.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into desired size loaf pan that has been greased and floured.
Fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done tested.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Place in dish.
Pour mushroom soup over this, then spoon 1 can Cheddar cheese soup on top.
Bake until bubbly at 300° or 350°.

title: date pecan rocks
directions: Cream butter or shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and water.
Mix well.
This makes a very stiff dough.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cherry pie filling chocolate cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix, oil and eggs with electric mixer until blended.
Add cherry pie filling and mix with electric mixer just until blended, so it breaks up the cherries some.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
This is a dense, moist cake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1/2 of the cornbread stuffing mix. Place in greased casserole.
Melt 1 stick butter or oleo in small skillet.
Use other half of stuffing and stir until well buttered. Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until crumbs are well browned.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; add egg, molasses and vinegar. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in.
Chill overnight. Roll out dough; cut in shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and pour into cake pan. Cut butter all over top and sprinkle cake mix over top.
Cook 1 hour or until top is brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and cocoa together and add to beaten egg yolks.
Last add sweet milk gradually.
Stir constantly while cooking until thick.
Put in a cooked pie crust and put meringue on top.
Return to oven and brown.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add the flour, broccoli and bay leaf.
Cook over medium heat until broccoli is tender, stirring frequently. Reduce heat; stir in the milk and pepper.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix and bake in a preheated 350° oven.
Frost with Orange Icing.

title: bow tie pasta and chicken
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil; add butter and chicken.
Saute until white (on both sides) until cooked.
Add broccoli, sun-dried tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Add white wine and chicken broth.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix in bow tie pasta.
(Cook pasta according to package.)
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage; drain. Let cool and mix with all the other cheeses and seasoning. Follow directions on hot roll mix, but only let rise once (5 minutes). Grease 2 small to medium cookie sheets. Separate dough in half and press out on each cookie sheet. (Dough should cover each cookie sheet.) Put half the sausage mixture on each, then roll into a log shape lengthwise. Brush each top with egg. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and brush the top of each with butter. Slice and serve.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic. Add water, catsup and all seasonings. Cover and simmer 2 hours. Mix flour with 1/4 cup water and add to meat mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cook noodles and drain. Mix with meat, leaving some meat for the top. Put in casserole. Cover and keep warm in oven until served. Enjoy!

title: hot dog tidbits
directions: Put flakes into a bowl.
Cut franks into 3/4-inch slices.
Dip each in catsup; roll in flakes until well coated.
Place in foil lined shallow pan; do not crowd.
Heat on grill for 20 minutes. Insert toothpick; serve hot on appetizer trays with catsup and/or mustard.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add 7 egg whites; stir.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes before serving.
Drizzle with Kraft caramel sauce.
May also top with whipped cream.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add milk; mix. Put in pie shell and bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: lime salad
directions: Add canned cream to cream cheese; blend well.
Add hot water to jello and stir until dissolved.
Combine the cream cheese with cream to the jello.
Add fruit and nuts.
Chill.

title: apple pudding dessert
directions: Beat together sugar, butter and egg.
Add flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and soda.
Stir in apple and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until soft, but not brown. Stir in flour and blend.
Add chicken stock, stirring constantly, and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and puree in food blender or processor.
Add peanut butter and half and half.
Return to low heat and heat thoroughly, stirring so it does not burn, but do not boil.

title: summer dills
directions: Combine salt, vinegar, water, pickling spice, and alum.
Set aside.
Put cucumber in 1 gallon jar, combining/alternating dill, garlic, and leaves, pack tight.
Pour liquid into jar.
Put in warm place for two weeks.
Refrigerate after opening.

title: phoenix chicken
directions: Saute breasts in olive oil until brown.
Combine Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and bake for 20 minutes. Sprinkle oregano and Mozzarella cheese over chicken.
Slice bell peppers and garnish.
Serve over wild rice.
Caramelize brown sugar and string over chicken.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together 3 times.
Cream shortening; add remaining sugar (1 1/4 cups) gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add vanilla and 3 tablespoons of the syrup; blend.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, beating until smooth.
Pour into pans lined with waxed paper and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch layers. Cool and ice.

title: french toast bundles
directions: You will also need nonstick spray coating.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese with sugar.
Mix with pineapple.
Prepare Dream Whip accordingly and fold into pineapple mixture.
Pour into crust and chill for several hours.

title: slow cooker lasagna
directions: Cook beef and Italian seasoning in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring until beef crumbles; drain. Combine spaghetti sauce and water in a bowl. Place 4 uncooked noodles in bottom of a lightly greased 5-quart electric slow cooker. Layer with half each of beef mixture and spaghetti sauce mixture. Spread cottage cheese over beef and spaghetti sauce. Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Layer with remaining noodles, meat, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Cover and cook on HIGH setting 1 hour; reduce heat and cook on LOW setting 5 hours. Yield: 4 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco, then add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add this to the mixture alternately with the cup of milk.
Add vanilla and 1 cup of coconut.
Bake in a 315° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Brown meat, drain and set aside.
Stir meal, milk, eggs, corn, Ro-Tel tomatoes and vegetable oil together.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased hot 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet.
Top evenly with beef, followed by the cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour remaining batter over the top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into wedges to serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and egg yolks, adding milk, margarine and vanilla.
Cook well and pour into baked pie shell.
Put meringue on top and brown.
Great!

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add the remainder of milk and the pudding mix.
Beat on low speed until blended, about 1 minute.
Pour at once into crumb crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, salt and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Sift flour and soda, gradually adding to first mixture.
Add pears and pecans; blend.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325° or 12 muffins and 1 loaf pan (2 mini loaf pans).

title: gerri's barbecue beans
directions: Mix beans, onions that have been sauteed in oil, garlic, catsup and molasses; place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with a layer of cheese.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly hot in a 350° oven.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Cream the cheese, butter, mayonnaise, garlic salt and seasoned salt together.
Add crabmeat and blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture on muffin halves.
Cut in quarters.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
When frozen, place in freezer bag and serve when needed. Broil 5 to 8 minutes and serve hot.

title: durgin park's indian pudding
directions: Heat 3 cups milk.
Stir in butter, molasses and honey.
Mix cornmeal and spices and stir gradually into warm milk mixture, using a wire whisk to avoid lumps.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes, or until thick.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Put pudding in an oiled ovenproof casserole.
Pour 1 cup milk over it.
Do not stir.
Bake for 3 hours.

title: garlic tomato sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a saucepan.
Heat on medium, stirring, until hot and bubbly.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.
Make 3 layers.

title: cauliflower-lettuce salad
directions: In a glass bowl, layer lettuce, cauliflower, bacon, onion and beans.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cheese.
Spread over the top of salad.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Toss when ready to serve.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with salt, pepper and onion.
Add potatoes, both cans of soup and water.
Cook until it starts to bubble.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of dish.
Add 1/2 package dressing.
Mix and add other ingredients.
Top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cut angel food or orange chiffon cake in middle and ice with mixture of ingredients.
Then cover outside with whipping cream or Dream Whip.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, juice and peel.
Mix until well blended. Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture; chill.
Layer fruit in 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in the order given.
May use electric mixer or spoon.
Chill 1 hour, or until firm.
Roll small amount of dough out at a time on floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Keep remaining dough in the refrigerator until ready to use.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef well and drain off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover and simmer until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortillas or corn chips.

title: pear preserves
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Add pears.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour according to pears.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Put in jars.
Seal and freeze or use two piece jar lids.
Boil flats, clean jar edges and place flat and ring on jars.
Process 10 minutes in water bath.

title: asparagus sauce
directions: Blend all together in a blender or food processor.
Pour over asparagus.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add margarine, sugar, milk, egg and apple.
Stir just to moisten (batter should look lumpy).
Fill greased muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Yields 10 to 11 muffins.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat oleo and sugar together.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: millionaire cake(pie)
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs as you would for crusts and pat into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemonade well.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and let set in refrigerator.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Melt butter but do not brown.
Add flour and gradually stir in milk.
Add chopped onion, almonds, sugar, salt and pepper. Cook together for 15 minutes over low heat.
Before serving fold in horseradish and if desired enrich with a little butter or cream.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add flour.
Beat in milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue baking for 45 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix together and spread on deep platter or big plate: cream cheese and sour cream.
Top in layers the finely chopped onion, green pepper, tomato, 1/2 cup grated cheese and salsa.
Use tortilla chips for dipping.

title: mrs. tobey's lemon chiffon pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
In double boiler, heat water, lemon rind and juice, sugar and salt.
Let sugar dissolve thoroughly.
When real hot, pour over egg yolks which have been beaten until thick. Return to double boiler; cook until thick custard.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Beat egg whites until stiff and dry, gradually adding another 1/2 cup of sugar.
Fold into custard and brown in oven.

title: italian zucchini soup
directions: Heat olive oil in a non-reactive medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add the onion and saute until translucent (5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, crushing against the side of the pan, and cook until water evaporates and tomatoes thicken, about 15 minutes.
Add zucchini, potato and enough water to cover the mixture by about 2-inches.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat to a simmer; season with salt and pepper.
Continue cooking until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: mel's hot pineapple salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and put in Pyrex dish.
Mix crackers and butter together and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with baked ham.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with pie crust or small biscuits.
Bake until crust or biscuits are done at 375°.

title: banana bread loaf
directions: In a bowl combine salt, flour, baking powder, and soda.
In another bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat vigorously until frothy.
Add bananas and blend thoroughly.
Fold into flour mixture until blended.
Pour into a greased bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, until crust is brown.
Use a toothpick to test for doneness (may require 15 to 20 minutes longer).
Remove pan to a rack.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Invert pan.
Cut into 1 inch slices.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: finnish turnips
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Into a blender or a large bowl, put turnip, salt, pepper, sugar, butter, milk, egg and a sprinkle of nutmeg.
Blend or beat well.
Turn into a buttered mold.
Cover with crushed cornflakes and dot with butter.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and baking powder.
Heat until very hot the milk and butter or oleo. Add to above ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in greased and floured pans (2 layer pans or loaf (sheet) pan).

title: lasagne
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add meat and brown; drain excess fat. Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer; cook noodles.
Drain.
Cool in cold water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Layer noodles, meat and cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix in casserole and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Variation:
Add 1 can mushroom slices.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Melt butter in cake pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients except spinach and cheese with mixer.
Fold in spinach and cheese.
Pour into cake pan over melted butter.
Sprinkle seasoned salt on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: simple cobbler
directions: In an 8 x 8 glass casserole dish, melt the butter in the microwave. Add flour, milk, sugar and cinnamon and stir slightly. Add can of fruit (liquid and all) and do not stir. Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until top begins to brown. Serve plain or with ice cream. Makes 6 to 8 servings. ENJOY.

title: no-fry french toast
directions: You will also need nonstick spray coating.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil, then remove from heat. Add 1 package semi-sweet morsels and vanilla.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining package of morsels and nuts (optional).
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and sugar.
Lastly, stir in diced apple.
Bake in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix in dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, nuts, coconut and egg whites.
Bake in three layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Whisk together the sesame seeds, poppy seeds, sugar, olive oil, vinegar, paprika, Worcestershire sauce and onions. Refrigerate until chilled. In a large bowl, combine the spinach, strawberries and almonds. Pour dressing over salad; toss and refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Boil all except oleo for 5 minutes.
Add oleo and set aside to cool.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Blend all ingredients, except salt and pepper, in blender and puree until almost smooth.
You may have to blend in batches. Pour into saucepan and heat slowly, stirring often, until almost a boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
This can be served hot or cold.
Garnish with parsley or dill sprigs.
Pass the croutons. This is a wonderful way to use all those cucumbers in the garden.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all vegetables. Mix together with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup vinegar and 1/4 cup oil.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In small bowl of 1/4 cup warm water, sprinkle active yeast on top; stir to dissolve.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining 2 1/2 cups warm water, brown sugar and vegetable oil. Stir in whole wheat flour and 1 cup white flour; beat well.
Stir in dissolved yeast.
Add 3 more cups of white flour to make a moderately stiff dough.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until medium done.
Rinse.
Arrange layers of carrots, green pepper and onion in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring until thoroughly blended.
Pour sauce over carrot mixture.
Refrigerate until flavor is absorbed.

title: baked beans
directions: Place bacon strips on broiler pan.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes per side.
Watch closely.
Remove from broiler and place on paper towel to drain off excess fat.
Cover a 2-quart casserole with cooking spray; set aside.
In large bowl, combine molasses, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Add beans and stir gently to blend.
Place several strips of bacon on bottom of casserole. Spoon beans in casserole to cover bacon strips.
Add bacon to cover beans.
Repeat process until all the beans and bacon have been used.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: banana oat bread
directions: In large bowl, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Mix flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas and milk.
Stir in oats and raisins. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Cool 10 minutes; turn out of pan, then cool completely.

title: hot dagos
directions: Mix in large kettle.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until thick as you want it. Put in jars and seal.

title: dreamsicle shake
directions: Put in blender until milkshake consistency.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Place milk, candy bars and marshmallows in top pan of double boiler and melt; cool completely. Fold half of Cool Whip into chocolate mixture. Pour into pie crust; top with remaining Cool Whip and chill in refrigerator for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Shake well before serving.
This is especially good on spinach salad and strawberries.

title: applenutter treats
directions: Mix peanut butter and cornflakes.
Slice the apples.
Spread the peanut butter mixture on each of the apple slices.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream Cheese Mixture:
Soften the cream cheese and butter; beat together.
Add sugar, 2 eggs, flour and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Set aside.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the flour, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Press evenly into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat other ingredients until light and fluffy; pour over hot crust.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: elaine's pasta recipe
directions: Combine tomatoes, Brie, basil, garlic, 1 cup olive oil and salt and pepper in a bowl. Prepare 2 hours before serving. Bring 6-quarts water to boil. Add 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add linguine. Drain pasta, and toss with tomato mixture.

title: fresh salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken-garlic-ziti(makes approximately 4 servings.  adjust accordingly!)
directions: Prepare the chicken.
Put oil in pan and heat.
Put chicken in oil and cook.
While cooking, add a generous amount of pepper and two big teaspoons of crushed garlic.
Stir, cover and let cook. Prepare the broccoli and steam.
Prepare the noodles and drain.

title: just peachy fruit salad
directions: Mix
all fruit together and add pie filling.
Refrigerate. Will keep several days.

title: artichoke dip
directions: To Microwave:
In 1-quart microwavable bowl, combine sour cream, cream cheese and mustard.
Stir in artichokes, pepper and chili powder.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until hot, stirring halfway through.
Garnish with green onions.
Serve with vegetables, crackers, tortillas or potato chips.

title: no sugar lemon sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine first three ingredients.
Slowly add boiling water, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Simmer stirring about 5 minutes or until clear and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and rest of ingredients.
Makes 1 cup.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add mushrooms, including water.
Stir in flour.
Add onion soup and gradually add water.
Simmer covered 10 minutes.
While simmering, prepare noodles.
Add sour cream to meat.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: apple crisp or apple candy pie
directions: Put apples and water in a deep baking dish (well buttered). Mix with a fork the flour, white or brown sugar, cinnamon, butter and salt.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and the crust is brown, about 30 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Mix beet juice; stir vinegar and remaining ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot spice mixture over eggs and beets; cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours to allow eggs to flavor.

title: cheese cake(spring-pan)
directions: Line bottom and about 1/2 of the side of the pan with crust.

title: dump cake
directions: You can also use blueberry pie filling.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and place half in a baking dish.
Cover with pastry.
Then add the rest of the mixture and cover with more pastry.
(Frozen pie shells make good pastry.)
Bake until pastry is golden brown at 400°.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Mix well and drop on wax paper.

title: helen's three-bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix the wet ingredients and the dry ingredients separately, then mix them together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a loaf pan or bake at 350° for 20 minutes in muffin pans.

title: the breakfast "recipe"
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside.
Beat eggs thoroughly. Add milk, salt, mustard and bread; mix.
Add cheese and sausage and mix well.
Bake in buttered pan (9 x 13-inch) for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together (cake mix, Dream Whip and cocoa).

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together. Mix rest of ingredients. Add sugar and cocoa; blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: janey's cathedral cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter together, then cool.
Add marshmallows.
Sprinkle flaked coconut onto a sheet of waxed paper. Spread one-third of the chocolate/marshmallow mixture onto the coconut.
Roll up into a cylinder shape.
Repeat twice, until you have three cylinders.
Chill.
Slice to serve.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions using two 8-inch cake pans. Cool and split layers. Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan. Add peaches and water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened. Cool completely. Combine whipping cream and powdered sugar in a medium mixing bowl. Beat until stiff peaks form. Spoon 1/3 of peach filling over split layer of cake. Spread 1/2 cup sour cream over filling. Repeat procedure with remaining cake layers, peach filling and sour cream, ending with remaining cake layer. Frost with sweetened whipped cream and garnish with fresh peach slices.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, flour, soda and buttermilk.
Alternate flour and buttermilk while mixing.
Fold in 2 cups raw rhubarb.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in flour mixture.
In skillet, brown chicken in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water; add with remaining lemon juice to skillet.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of wax paper; flatten to 1/2-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese in the center of each chicken piece.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of parsley.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with wooden picks.
Combine bread crumbs, paprika, salt and pepper.
Dip each chicken breast in milk.
Roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork, kraut and noodles
directions: *Wheat, if you can find them or homemade noodles, if you prefer and know how.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Separate biscuits; cut each into thirds.
Wrap dough around cheese cubes.
Seal well.
Fry in hot fat, 2 to 3 minutes until brown.
