Drain on towel.
Yields 30 appetizers.

title: chicken noodle soup salad
directions: Melt cream cheese in soup.
Add mayonnaise and let cool.
Heat jello in water and mix soup mixture into jello with electric beater.
Add 1 can shrimp or tuna.
Chill 2 hours.

title: cheezy chicken breasts(microwave)
directions: Cut 3-inch lengthwise slit in thickest part of each piece of chicken breast.
Cut cheese into 4 sticks and insert one into slit of each piece.
Close with a toothpick.
Place breast pieces, bone side down, in a microwavable dish.
Brush with egg.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over chicken.
Microwave 12 minutes, rotating once if you do not have a turntable to use.

title: venison roast
directions: Cook venison until tender in water.
Add salt and pepper. Cool.
Cut into small pieces.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine oatmeal and buttermilk in large bowl.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add other ingredients to mixture; mix well.
Spray muffin pan with Pam or use muffin cups.
If so, put 3 drops of oil in each cup.
Fill each cup full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds and membrane from green peppers. Precook in salted, boiling water 5 minutes. Sprinkle inside with salt; place in baking dish.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Brown meat in shortening in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender.

title: meat turnovers
directions: Brown meat, drain fat, add sprouts, chestnuts, and onions and simmer for a few minutes. Add gravy and remove from heat Place in fridge for 1 hour.

title: fool's toffee
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Melt 1 cup butter and brown sugar. Boil for 4 minutes.
Line tray with saltine crackers. Drizzle the butter-sugar mixture on top of crackers and spread. Bake 5 minutes at 350°. Drop
the chocolate chips on top. When melted, smooth over and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Freeze for 15 minutes. Break apart.

title: deer bake
directions: Put meat in oblong baking dish.
Pour remaining ingredients over top of meat.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 4 hours, or until meat is tender.

title: veggie bars
directions: Lay crescent rolls out flat on jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese.
Add salad dressing and dry Ranch mix.
Spread over rolls.
Chop vegetables and layer over top of cheese.
Cut into bars.

title: break away bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix Crisco and boiling water; let melt.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, yeast and flour. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
The next day, divide dough into 2 equal parts.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each biscuit into melted butter, one at a time.
Line Bundt pan with biscuits on end and cover with a damp towel.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chili burritos
directions: Heat chili on medium until it bubbles.
Fill tortilla with chili and cheese.
Fold ends of tortilla up about 1 1/2 inches and roll into a burrito.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, onions, cheese, sour cream and salsa.
Serve with a fork!!!

title: christmas egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks; gradually add 1 cup sugar and the salt, beating
constantly.
Gradually add milk and cream.
Cook over hot water,
stirring
constantly
until
mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Cool.
Add	vanilla
and
chill.
To serve, beat egg whites
until
foamy.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/2 cup sugar and fold into chilled custard.
Spoon into chilled punch bowl and sprinkle
with nutmeg.
Yield:
4 quarts or 30 servings.

title: marinated steak italiano
directions: In large, shallow non-aluminum baking dish or plastic bag, pour 1/2 cup Italian dressing over steak.
Cover, or close bag, and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 3 to 24 hours. Remove steak from marinade, discarding marinade.
Grill or broil steak, turning once and brushing frequently with remaining dressing, until steak is done.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: chocolate smoothie
directions: Mix butter and powdered sugar.
Cream thoroughly.
Add beaten egg yolks, vanilla and chocolate.
Mix thoroughly.
Add egg whites.
Beat all together.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Mix sugar and water and boil together until syrup spins a thread, then continue cooking slowly until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add grated orange rind and stir until foamy.
Stir in shelled pecans, being sure candy coats each one.
Pour onto lightly greased dish.
Nuts may be separated using 2 forks while candy is still warm or you may let candy cool and harden, then break into lumps.

title: ham and potato soup
directions: Put ham in just enough water to cover.
Boil until meat falls off the bone.
Remove bone, then add the onions and potatoes. Cook until potatoes are done and the water has cooked down some. Take a potato masher and squash the potatoes until crumbled, not mashed.
Add milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cocoa swirl coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, cocoa and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter.
Beat in cream cheese,
1 1/2 cups sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, baking powder and raisins, stirring until smooth.
Generously grease a 10-inch tube pan and sprinkle pecans over bottom.
Spoon 1/2 batter into pan.
Cover with 1/2 cup cinnamon-cocoa mixture. Spoon remaining batter into pan.
Top with remaining cinnamon-cocoa mixture.
Bake at 325° for 65 to 75 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Invert cake onto wire rack to finish cooling.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: tasty cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: chicken valentina
directions: Rinse chicken
and pat dry. On a plate, spoon the 2 tablespoons olive oil. Roll chicken in oil.
On another plate, put bread crumbs and salt and pepper. Roll chicken that was in the oil into bread crumbs. Pour remaining oil from plate onto bottom of glass baking pan. Place chicken in pan.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in shallow greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: nachos
directions: Cube cheese; mix all ingredients.
Melt slowly in microwave on High.
Serve over nacho chips.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook together for 2 hours or until desired thickness. Stir often.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and stir, mixing well.
Pat lightly in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef in large glass bowl.
Cook at high 2 to 3 minutes or until beef is browned; stir once.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, oregano and garlic powder.
Cook at high 4 to 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Meanwhile, combine Ricotta cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce into 12 x 8-inch dish. Alternately layer noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce, forming 3 layers.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: carrot cake ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. Into large bowl mix first 11 ingredients.
Mix at low until just mixed.
Increase to high for 4 minutes, scraping bowl.
With rubber spatula fold in carrots, walnuts and raisins.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Let cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: elizabeth's pork chop casserole
directions: In a large frying pan, scramble and brown meat and onions. Add flour, bouillon, soy sauce. Mix well. Add vegetables and mushrooms. Add water and let simmer until thickened to desired thickness. Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed on package in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Immediately after removing from oven, poke holes in 1-inch intervals with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand condensed milk and caramel ice cream toping over cake. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed Heath bars. Better served at room temperature.

title: peanut butter swirls
directions: Mix all ingredients except melted chocolate chips.
Divide dough.
Place dough on waxed paper.
Put another sheet of waxed paper on top and roll dough in 15 x 8 x 1/4-inch rectangle.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger slightly with shortening.
Put into large baking dish.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with noodles.
Noodles may be added last 15 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bowl; wash and allow to dry.
Dressing: Into food process or blender, place mustard, oil, crushed garlic, red wine vinegar and anchovies.
Blend until fully mixed.
Toss over lettuce and serve with croutons and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: easy camp stew
directions: Heat all meats, corn and tomatoes.
Add to potatoes and onion. Season to taste.
Simmer on top of stove for about 1 hour or in crock-pot on low for several hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Shape into loaf and place in well-greased pan.
Place sliced carrots around meat.
Cover and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Add sliced or quartered potatoes and cover.
Bake 30 more minutes or until potatoes are done.
Remove cover and brown, approximately 10 minutes.

title: no-fuss caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and margarine in a 4 cup glass measure cup.
Place in microwave oven and bring to a boil on High for 2 to 4 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Spray small grocery type bag with Pam and put 3 quarts of popped corn into bag and pour hot mixture over corn in bag.
Place in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake; microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Place in microwave on Roast/Medium for 1/2 to 1 minute.
Shake; microwave 1/2 minute again.
Spread on hot cookie sheet.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch casserole with Pam.
Moisten 3/4 of the stuffing mix with some of the chicken broth.
Pat down evenly in casserole.
Place diced chicken on top.
In medium size bowl, combine soup and 1/2 soup can of white wine.
Mix sour cream, mushrooms, green onions, salt and pepper; pour over chicken.
Mix remaining stuffing mix with 1 stick butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili-cheese balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake until set, 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen appetizers.

title: dual potato gratin
directions: Spoon garlic mashed potatoes evenly into 4 lightly greased, 4-inch gratin dishes, reserving 3/4 cup mashed potatoes.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add half of potatoes in a single layer and cook 2 minutes on each side or until tender. Drain on paper towels.
Repeat procedure with remaining potatoes. Layer potato slices around outside edges of mashed potatoes, forming circles.
Roll reserved mashed potatoes into balls, placing in center.
Coat gratins with cooking spray and sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Garnish with chives.
(Three cups regular mashed potatoes can be substituted.)

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and saut onion. Add rice and saut until rice turns golden (about 3 minutes). Put in casserole dish. Add remaining ingredients, all the juice. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes. Cook until moisture is gone. Do not overcook.

title: cranberry nut cheese ball
directions: Combine 1/2 cup dried cranberries, 1/2 cup nuts, ginger, orange peel, orange juice and cream cheese.
Shape into ball; wrap in plastic wrap and chill 1 hour.
Roll sides of ball in 1/2 cup chopped nuts and press 1/2 cup dried cranberries into top.
Serve with crackers and celery sticks.
Fat-free cream cheese works well.

title: chicken and sausage casserole
directions: Boil the chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove from bones and cut in small pieces.
Brown sausage and drain. Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken marsala with angel hair pasta
directions: Brown the chicken breasts in the olive oil in a large skillet. Remove the chicken from the skillet.
Cook and stir the vegetables and garlic in the same skillet over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in the sauce and white wine, then add the chicken and cover.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer 20 minutes.
Season as desired with salt and pepper.
Prepare the angel hair pasta as directed on package.
Serve the chicken breasts and sauce over the pasta and sprinkle with parsley.
This recipe makes 4 servings with a preparation time of 15 minutes and a cooking time of 30 minutes.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, cream cheese and milk. Heat.
Add cooked macaroni, vegetables and Parmesan cheese.
Heat thoroughly and serve.
Very good!

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat peanut butter, vanilla, margarine and salt until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then confectioners sugar until smooth.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheets.
Chill until firm.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and ground beef.
Add onions and saut.
Add all seasonings and all beans.
Place all in crock-pot and simmer.

title: burger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a flameproof casserole, heat olive oil.
When hot, add garlic, onion and carrots; saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, thyme and ham; saute for a minute more; season to taste with pepper.
Stir in beans and add just enough water to cover the beans.
Bring liquid to a boil; cut back to a simmer.
Cover and place in oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover casserole; sprinkle with crumbs and bake for 30 minutes to an hour more or until beans have absorbed liquid and top is somewhat crusty.

title: sour cream coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch heavy Bundt pan.
Cream margarine and 2 cups of the sugar.
Add eggs, blending well; add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into creamed mix and beat just until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Mix remaining 3/4 cup sugar with pecans and cinnamon in a separate small bowl.
Layer coffeecake mix, pecans, coffeecake mix and pecans in Bundt pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour. Serve warm.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then wet ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
As soon as it is out of oven, top with 2 cups nuts and 2 cups marshmallows.

title: make ahead spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix with eggs, butter and Parmesan cheese while spaghetti is still hot.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of cottage cheese.
Brown meats and drain.
Mix meats with spaghetti sauce.
Pour meat sauce into pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight (or for a few hours).
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: toffee bars or heath bars
directions: Grease bottom of 9-inch square pan and pour chopped nuts over bottom.
Combine brown sugar and butter and cook to 270° (hard ball stage) or 4 to 5 minutes, after coming to a boil.
Pour over nuts and spread evenly.
Pour chocolate chips over mixture and cover for 2 to 4 minutes (until melted).
Spread out evenly and put in refrigerator until cold.
Break into pieces and keep cool.

title: cheesy potato casserole(lo-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Add potatoes and cheese; stir mixture well. Spoon potato mixture into a 13 x 9 baking dish coated with cooking spray. Top with potato chips. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or until thoroughly heated and lightly browned.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix the cheese, egg, milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce for the topping and set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Gently saute carrot and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: vondell's easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, egg, oil and flour.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Spoon in greased muffin tins and bake at 400°.
Makes 24 large rolls.

title: oven fries italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a baking sheet with foil and lightly grease the foil.
Cut the potatoes lengthwise into 1/2 inch thick wedges.
Melt the butter on the stove.
In a large bowl, combine melted butter, oil, garlic, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add the potatoes and toss to coat well with the herbed butter.
Arrange potatoes on the baking sheet.
Sprinkle evenly with the Parmesan.
Bake the potatoes for about 30 minutes or until they are tender and golden.
Move the potatoes around to ensure even cooking.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with apple wedges.

title: pull-apart herb bread
directions: In a skillet, saute the garlic in the butter and set aside. Separate the biscuits and place half of them in an even layer in a greased 9 inch springform pan.
Brush them with the garlic/butter mixture, and sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Combine the herbs and sprinkle half of them over the biscuits.
Repeat.
Place the pan on a baking sheet and bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and serve warm.

title: bul ko ki
directions: In mixing bowl (with lid) combine meat, lemon juice and sugar. Mix well and put in refrigerator for 5 to 6 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put it back in the refrigerator for another 5 to 6 hours.
Cook meat in a skillet at medium-high heat.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir hot water, 4 teaspoons butter and vegetable seasoning packet until melted.
Add crumbs and egg.
Spoon stuffing into cooked chicken breast, roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Put remaining stuffing in center of pan.
Brush chicken with melted butter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Warm soup and water; serve over chicken.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Press mixture into a 2 cup mold.
Chill several hours.
Unmold.
Serve with crackers.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water 24 hours, then wash in cold water.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Drop by
teaspoons on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix butter, flour and milk in saucepan, stir over low heat until creamy. Lay half of the potatoes and onions in a greased cassarole dish. Pour half of the mixture over potatoes, then add another layer of potates and onions, then add remaining mixture. Bake at 350° covered for about an hour, uncover bake till golden brown. Enjoy!

title: chevrie (goat cheese) fudge
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
When it is melted, fold it into cheese mixture with pecans.
Spread into a buttered 8-inch baking pan.
Chill until ready to serve.
Cut in squares.
Yields about 48 pieces.

title: cold salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper over heat.
Bring to boil until sugar is melted clear.
Set aside.
Mix all vegetables together in big bowl.
Pour liquid over vegetables.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour or longer.
Serve cold.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend last 6 ingredients.
Layer cookies and pudding mixture, cookies and pudding mixture.

title: almond crisp
directions: Butter a cookie sheet.
Place graham cracker pieces on bottom of pan.
Mix butter and brown sugar and boil on low for 3 minutes. Pour and spread mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 325° about 5 minutes when mixture will bubble.
Cool and serve.

title: meat lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse under cold running water.
Brown meat in frypan over medium heat.
Drain.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, green onions and noodles.
Alternate layers of noodles with meat mixtures in greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: kartoffel suppe(potato soup)
directions: Peel, wash and dice the potatoes.
Clean, wash and chop the pot herbs; chop the onion.
Cook all until tender in 2 pints salted water and rub through a sieve.
Make a thickening of butter and flour.
Stir into the soup and cook for a few minutes. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: quick popsicles
directions: Mix hot water, Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar together. Stir until dissolved, then add cold water.
You can use popsicle holders or Dixie cups and sticks. These are softer than the kind you buy in the store and come in handy for a sick child or just for fun.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour, egg yolks, Crisco and milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Cook at 325° until brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion with margarine in skillet.
Add ground beef, after browned, drain.
Simmer all the ingredients for approximately 1 hour.
While this simmers, cook lasagna noodles by directions on box.
Then place 1 layer of noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
On this layer, put a layer of sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Continue layering until all is used.
Don't put noodles on top layer.
Have sauce and cheese on top.

title: easy minestrone soup
directions: Cook ground beef with onions.
Drain fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Set on low and simmer.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Add chicken to 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Mix and let stand for 1 hour in the refrigerator. Brown chicken in oil, reserving marinade (soy sauce and lemon juice).
Add reserved marinade and 3/4 cup broth.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes. Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Combine 1/4 cup reserved pineapple juice, brown sugar, ginger, cornstarch, vinegar, remaining broth and remaining soy sauce.
Add to chicken.
Cook until sauce thickens and clears, stirring constantly.
Cut bell pepper into thin strips and onion into eighths.
Add to chicken and cook until tender crisp.
Add pineapple and water chestnuts. Cook until warm.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet and sour fondue
directions: Mix first 3 dry ingredients together.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir in dry ingredients; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Pour in chafing or fondue pot; add precooked smoky sausage (cut into bite size pieces).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; roll in additional nuts.

title: cranberry-raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add all ingredients, except sour cream, and stir well.
Add sour cream to blend, if desired. Chill until firm.

title: orange cottage cheese mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into oblong pan or 8 individual molds.
Chill until set.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all in saucepan and cook over medium heat until well blended.
Sauce is excellent for grilled foods, mixed with hamburger before cooking, for roast in crock-pot and for shredded beef sandwiches.

title: pina colada cheese cake
directions: *You will need 2 (19 ounce) cans of Dole crushed pineapple in juice or syrup.

title: amish buttermilk or sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs. Stir dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk or sour cream. Bake at 350°.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spoon over fruit mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bearnaise sauce(french)
directions: Serve with beef or fish.
Yields 1 1/2 cups (6 tablespoon per serving).

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sour cream.
Chill slightly until thick.
Fold in sour cream.
Delicious with meat dish!

title: possum and sweet potatoes
directions: Fatten possum for 2 weeks on cornbread and buttermilk.
Kill and clean possum.
Boil possum 30 minutes in salt water.
Boil sweet potatoes; cut in halves.
Place possum in baking dish; put sweet potatoes around possum.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Baste with natural juices.
Best served with turnip greens and biscuits.

title: cheese spinach souffle
directions: Stir all the ingredients together and put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: golden potato-cheese squares
directions: Cook the potatoes until tender.
Once they are done, preheat the oven to 350°.
Put the potatoes (at this point, peel the skins, if desired) in a larger mixing bowl with the margarine and a little of the milk.
Mash until smooth.
Add the remaining milk and the rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour the mixture into an oiled large shallow baking casserole and pat smooth. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Allow to stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then cut into squares and serve.

title: cheddar cheese potato soup
directions: On medium-low heat in a 3-quart saucepan, saute the celery and onions in the butter until the onions are tender.
Take care not to brown the onions.
Add chicken broth, potatoes and the water. Place on medium-low heat and cook until potatoes are very soft and tender.
When the potatoes are done, add the chicken bouillon cubes and cook until the cubes have dissolved.
Mash potatoes slightly, but leave most in chunks.
Reduce heat and add half and half.
Stir mixture.
Add shredded cheese and stir until the cheese is completely melted and dissolved into mixture.
Sprinkle sugar, pepper and salt into soup.
Stir well.
Let soup simmer very slow for 20 to 30 minutes, taking care not to let soup scorch.
When ready to serve, garnish with shredded Colby or Jack cheese and parsley.
Serve with a crisp salad and hard rolls.
What a meal.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain; reserve 1/3 cup liquid, adding water, if necessary.
Stir bouillon granules into reserved liquid.
In a blender container, combine broccoli, reserved broccoli liquid and sour cream. Cover. Blend until smooth, scraping down sides as necessary. Pour broccoli mixture into saucepan.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Heat through.
Transfer to fondue pot.
Place over fondue burner.
Serve with raw vegetables, crackers or breadsticks. Makes 2 cups.

title: jalapeno peppers
directions: Place a few peppers at a time in skillet with just enough grease to cover bottom of pan. Blister the skins; set aside on paper towel to drain and absorb grease. Place a few cooked carrot nickels (slices) in bottom of pint jar; add peppers, 1/2 tsp. salt, pinch of basil and small piece of garlic in each jar. Boil equal amounts of water and vinegar and pour over peppers. Seal jars. If you desire, you can process with a water bath for 5 minutes to set seal. (No longer than 5 minutes or they will be soft.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, cheese, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix with broccoli and pour into buttered casserole.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in a saucepan and add dry stuffing mix.
Stir to blend. spread on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Use 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spiced crackers
directions: Mix all spices and oil together.
Put 2 packs of crackers into 1 zip lock bag; add 3/4 cup oil mixture.
Shake well; turn bag over and over until oil is absorbed.
Repeat
for the remaining crackers and oil mixture. Crackers are good with gumbo and tuna.

title: warm cranapple cinnamon punch
directions: Warm the cranapple juice and cinnamon sticks, stirring occasionally.
Next, add cinnamon candies to taste.
Add vodka. Stir until cinnamon candies dissolve.
Serve warm, keeping punch over low flame.
Do not bring to boil.

title: sizzling rice egg drop soup
directions: In a pot cook chicken stock, vinegar, soy sauce, pepper and salt; bring to a boil.

While boiling, fry rice in a skillet in thin layers until you get a crust that is crispy and golden brown. When soup has boiled for a few minutes, mix cornstarch and water; add to soup and let thicken slightly (about 5 minutes).
Slowly dribble beaten egg into the soup, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
While soup is hot, add the hot fried rice cakes and serve.
The key to make the soup sizzle is to put hot rice cakes in the hot soup.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown onions in a hot nonstick skillet.
Layer a small casserole with onions and beans.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour mixture over beans and onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 serving (10 calories).

title: banana split
directions: Crush crackers and mix with 6 tablespoons melted oleo.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next 4 ingredients until fluffy. Spread over crust and chill 1 hour.
Slice bananas on top.
Drain pineapple and put on top of bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Top it with nuts and cherries.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper beef; place in Dutch oven sprayed with vegetable spray.
Surround with vegetables.
Combine Sloppy Joe mix with tomato juice; pour over roast.
Cover with a tight fitting lid.
Roast in preheated oven at 400° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; allow to stand for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil
water
and
sugar
until
dissolved.
Cool.
Add blended bananas to fruit juices quickly before they turn dark. Mix all
ingredients together and freeze until slushy.
Add 3 quarts ginger
ale just before serving.
Can be made ahead of time
and thawed to a slushy stage before serving.
Serves 25 to 30 with seconds.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to rolling boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cornflakes.
Stir to coat well.
Pour out on waxed paper to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into thin pieces.
Put oil, ginger and garlic into electric skillet or wok.
Brown a little at a time.
Drain meat well.
Slice onion and pepper.
Add to grease and saute.
Add cooked meat and toss slightly.
Add mushrooms and water chestnuts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, melt half the package of chocolate chips and butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Spread or brush the melted chocolate over the bottom and up the side of pastry shell. Chill.

title: tuna dip mold
directions: Combine
all
ingredients into a mold except the walnut halves,
leave
them for covering the whole mold.
Set in nice soup bowl.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: chop meat soup
directions: Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Stir in milk, gradually with wooden spoon, while cooking on low heat until pudding thickens.
Use wire whisk to prevent lumps.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: aroma of christmas(potpourri)
directions: Combine and simmer.
Add water as needed.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Put in casserole and cover with onion rings. Beat the soup until creamy and pour over top of beans and onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corned beef mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine all other ingredients and place in 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or more. Spread on your favorite cracker.

title: swedish nut bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with tortilla chips. This will last for days in the refrigerator.

title: easy caramel fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, heat 1 cup sugar until it is liquid and light brown.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly, then stir in the remaining sugar and Milnot.
Cook over low heat until soft boil stage.
Then add soda.
Stir vigorously.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until candy loses its gloss and is thick.
Add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, buttered.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Pour condensed milk in large bowl.
Add lemon juice; stir until thickened.
Add drained pineapple, chopped pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate until set.

title: pumpkin nut coffeecake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix at low speed for 1 minute.
Mix 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: chicken caprese salad
directions: Heat pan over medium heat.
Rub chicken with balsamic vinegar to tenderize.
Cook chicken breasts for 4-5 minutes on each side. Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes to come to room temperature.
Top each breast with a layer of tomato, basil, and cheese (2 pieces each to 1 piece chicken).
Drizzle the entire dish with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serve with crusty bread.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, milk, cheese, onion and pepper; heat until cheese melts.
In a 2-quart dish, layer potatoes and soup; cover.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix, grease and flour pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix chilled ginger ale and cranberry juice in a punch bowl. Add vanilla and orange slices.
Stir.
When ready to serve, add ice cubes or block of ice.

title: pasta with shrimp and vegetables
directions: Cook broccoli and bell pepper in large pot of boiling water until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.
Transfer to a bowl of ice water using slotted spoon and cool.
Drain.
Return water in pot to boil.
Add pasta and cook until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally.
Drain reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid.
Add oil, garlic, rosemary and dried red pepper to same pot; stir 10 seconds over medium heat.
Add shrimp. Saute until cooked through, about 3 minutes.
Return pasta to pot.
Add vegetables and reserved cooking liquid; toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

title: slam dunk crab dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until smooth. Stir in crab, onions, red pepper, curry powder and garlic salt. Refrigerate until serving.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: ranch ball spread
directions: Chop onions and beef.
Blend with cream cheese.
Add ranch dressing.
Then roll into a ball, then roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, cooking oil and egg; set aside. In another bowl, mix together remaining ingredients in given order; add together with pumpkin mixture. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: banana carrot bread
directions: Combine banana, sugar, oil and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold into banana mixture.
Stir in carrots and nuts. Spoon into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf
pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Wrap.
Store overnight before cutting.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Fry onions, garlic and celery until soft and brown. Add chicken and cook until water runs out. Add eggs (scrambled up). Boil and strain manicotti. Stuff shells and place in casserole. Cover with Ragu and add shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour over vegetables and mix.

title: grand prairie salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows.
Boil mixture slowly until marshmallows dissolve.
Let set slightly. Add cheese, pecans, pineapple and whipped cream.
Chill until set.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper the pork chops.
Roll in flour.
Place in a casserole dish (with cover).
Place a large slice of onion on each chop; top with a ring of pepper.
Place 2 tablespoons rice in each pepper ring.
Add celery, tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and steam slowly until chops are tender.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Slowly add sherbet and melt.
Drain oranges and add to mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma crane's dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in jars.
Put a lot of dill on top of jars, then pour boiling hot brine over them and seal.
Pickles ready in 8 to 10 weeks.

title: eggless, sugar-free strawberry ice cream
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze as directed.

title: cherry cheesecake cups
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, and vanilla together.
Put 2 vanilla wafers in each muffin cup.
Fill 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.
Cool and add cherry pie filling.
Makes 24.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar. Sift flour and soda. Add to egg mixture. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Cut up frying
chicken
or
if
chicken is already cut, wash and clean.
Drain;
mix
all
of
the
ingredients flour, salt, pepper,
Accent,
garlic,
poultry
seasoning and flour. Shake chicken in
flour
mixture
until
well
covered, in the cooking oil that has
been
placed in a frypan and heated hot. Place chicken in frypan and cook over medium-high fire until a golden brown is
reached,
from
to
minutes
or until chicken is done.
Remove from cooking oil and drain on a paper towel. A favorite dish the world over.

title: meaty cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in large skillet.
Stir until crumbling.
Drain and return to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges and boil 10 minutes.
Drain and put in buttered casserole dish.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and sugar together; mix with cabbage.
Dot with butter and pour hot milk over cabbage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and chop into small pieces.
Layer in bottom of casserole dish.
Drain Veg-All; pour over chicken.
In a small bowl, mix soup and 1 cup
milk; pour over Veg-All and chicken.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift together four times. Add 1 cup Miracle Whip salad dressing, 3/4 cup boiling water and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat ingredients until smooth. Pour into cake pans and bake at 350° until cake is done in center.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Mix in flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle top with chocolate bits.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
(This cake is very rich and needs no additional icing.
Just sprinkle the top with confectioners sugar after the cake cools.)

title: salmon patties
directions: Take bone out of salmon. In large mixing bowl, combine salmon, crackers, egg, onion, salt and pepper; mix well. Mixture will be moist. Shape into patties. In deep skillet, fry at 350 degrees in 1/2 inch of vegetable oil until golden brown on both sides.

title: mushroom canapes
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms and butter.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Add sauteed ingredients. Remove crust from day-old bread.
Roll each slice thin with rolling pin.
Spread each slice with mushroom mixture and roll up. Cut into 3 to 4 pieces.
Store in freezer until ready to use. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. (May freeze up to 6 months.)
Serves 40 to 50.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix, roll and cut.
Bake at 325°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix all together and put in baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs or croutons.
Bake 1/2 hour or until cheese is bubbly.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter and cream with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until golden brown and top cracks.
Not done until top cracks.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook the meat and cook the noodles.
Add tomatoes and sauces to meat and onion.
Cover bottom of pan and layer noodles with meat sauce, cottage cheese, shredded Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: jerry clower's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add alternately dry ingredients with milk/vanilla mixture.
Spoon drop (about a tablespoon in size) onto slightly greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 13 minutes, depending on how large the cakes are.

title: endive tomato salad
directions: To prepare dressing, combine oil, vinegars and water in a small bowl. Whisk until thickened; set aside. Arrange tomato slices in center of round platter. Sprinkle with basil and parsley. Tuck endive leaves under tomato slices, arranging like spokes in a wheel. Drizzle dressing over salad. Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Mix and bring to boil.

title: caroline spenser's sweet pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers 1/4-inch thick and soak for 24 hours. Wash well to remove lime.

title: eureka chew-chews
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter in saucepan and bring to boil. Boil 5 minutes until caramelized.
Pour mixture over crust and pecans.
Bake until bubbly.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over hot mixture.
Gently swirl chocolate chips with spatula to give marble effect.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Roll hamburger meat into small balls.
Mix other ingredients together. Pour over hamburger meat.
Put in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
To serve, use toothpicks.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake 9-inch pie crust and put aside to cool; combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir until blended, then add water and food coloring. Cook over medium heat until thick.
When completely cool, pour over strawberries that have been placed in cooled pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Drain fruits separately.
With hand, mash pineapple more.
Mix together cranberries, pineapple and orange.
Refrigerate.
Add nuts the day you serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well. Serve with raw veggies.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add cottage cheese to orange Jell-O.
Mix well, then add fruits, drained and mix well.
Last add Cool Whip and mix very well.
Makes a large bowl; good for P.T.O. or large gatherings. Refrigerate overnight.

title: tr. debby's perfect chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Beat in the egg. Stir in flour and baking soda.
Add the rolled oats and the chocolate chips.
Refrigerate the dough for about 10 minutes. Spoon out dough to the size cookie you want and roll it slightly in your hands to make it ball shape.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Makes 32 small cookies.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: erik's seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.

title: spaghetti dinner
directions: Cook until tender the chopped celery and onion in oil or shortening.
Add sliced frankfurters and brown lightly.
Stir in tomato soup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes or until desired thickness.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti.
Pour frankfurter mixture over spaghetti.

title: homemade pickle
directions: Sprinkle salt over sliced cucumbers, onion, bell pepper.
Cover and keep in refrigerator for 2-3 days.
Drain, add vinegar sugar and celery seed.
(Do not cook.)
Mix well - keep in refrigerator.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut slits through the roast and insert in them slivers of garlic and onion.
Put roast in a bowl and pour vinegar over. Place in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Then discard vinegar. Brown in heavy iron pot until nearly burned on all sides.
Then pour 2 cups coffee over roast; add 2 cups water and cover.
Cook slowly 6 hours at simmer.
Twenty minutes before serving, add salt and pepper and gin or whiskey, if desired.

title: macaroni-beef skillet supper
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Saute meat, onion and garlic in oil until meat is cooked and onion is tender.
Drain.
Add pepper, tomato sauce, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and Italian seasoning.
Bring mixture to a boil, then gently simmer for about 5 minutes. Mix in cooked macaroni and simmer for 5 more minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: In Dutch oven or deep frying pan, heat butter and oil.
Brown chicken adding salt and pepper on all pieces.
Remove chicken and set aside.

title: red snapper parmesan
directions: Place fish in greased baking dish.
Combine all but paprika and spread over.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown meat and onion together.
Add soups; stir all together.
Place noodles in bottom of casserole. Spread meat and soup mixture over noodles.
Put cheese on top. Bake at 300° until cheese melts.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter or oil.
Add chicken and brown a little.
Add paprika, hot pepper, salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Simmer slowly until fork-tender, about 1 hour.
Cook until thick.
Add sour cream.
Remove from fire.
Put chicken back in gravy.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: ann's clam chowder
directions: Cover potatoes and carrots with water.
Add salt and cook until tender.
Dice and simmer bacon, onion, celery and green pepper until all are soft.
In soup pot, place remaining ingredients.
Add potatoes and carrots and their water to the pot.
Add the bacon mixture to the pot.
Simmer for a few minutes to mix flavors.

title: mama's boiled custard
directions: Warm the milk in a heavy saucepan.
Do this very slowly and stir constantly until milk is lukewarm.
In a bowl, beat the eggs until well beaten.
Mix in the sugar, stir well.
Add the egg mixture very slowly to the warm milk while stirring constantly. Cook over medium-high heat until it coats a silver spoon.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Let cool and refrigerate.

title: 6 weeks muffins
directions: Mix well in large Tupperware bowl.
Store in refrigerator. Take out amount to be used at each baking.
May add nuts, pineapple, fresh apples etc. at that time.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in large brown grocery bag.
Mix sugar, syrup, butter and salt (if needed).
In 2-quart microwave dish, cook in microwave on High until it boils (about 2 minutes).
Turn dish and cook another 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir until mixture becomes light and foamy.
Pour over popped corn in bag and shake well.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake well.
Cook another minute on High.
Remove and shake. Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown the beef and pour off the grease.
Add all the ingredients except the cheese and chips.
Stir all the ingredients together and boil for 15 minutes.
Pour the chips into the mixture and stir well.
Put in a large casserole and sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ila's pickled okra
directions: Pack okra in hot sterilized Mason jars (I use 1/2 pint jars; can use pint jars).
Add a clove of garlic, 1 red pepper, 1 green pepper and 1 teaspoon dill seed to each jar.
Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over okra. Seal.
Let set 6 to 8 weeks before serving.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Add ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: deviled shark
directions: Melt butter in skillet at 250°.
Place 4 shark steaks in skillet.
Sprinkle lemon, teriyaki sauce and seasoning across top of steaks.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes each side.

title: much lighter chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a medium saucepan.
Add flour and stir over medium heat for 1 minute.
Do not brown.
Add chicken stock and nonfat milk.
Whisk over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add salt, garlic powder and pepper; continue to cook for 1 minute more.
In mixing bowl, combine sauce, chicken, mayonnaise, celery, onion, lemon juice and rice.
Mix well and pour into a casserole sprayed with Pam.
Top with almonds and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: instant doughnut balls
directions: Quarter biscuits and roll pieces into balls. Have oil hot enough for deep fry. Drop biscuits into hot oil until golden brown. Drain and roll doughnut balls into powdered sugar.

title: ham-asparagus casserole
directions: Blend soup with cream.
Add ham and asparagus.
Pour into 4 individual ramekins or a small shallow baking dish. Top with crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: appetizer
directions: On ungreased baking sheet, add one pineapple chunk on top of one slice water chestnut.
Wrap small piece bacon over pineapple and water chestnut.
Put toothpick to hold in place.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.
Serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Put beans in casserole.
Put in brown sugar.
Fry bacon crisp, then break into small pieces and mix altogether in casserole.
Put onion in center of beans and bake slowly for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are getting dry.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together; do not overmix or will become crumbly and dry. Place in pre-lined mold and cap.

title: milkless, eggless and butterless cake
directions: In large saucepan, boil first 5 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend remaining ingredients together and add to liquid part.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
May use Bundt or 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Check with toothpick.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Lightly grease foil lined 9-inch square pan.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan; add sugar and corn syrup.
Blend well.
Cook over medium low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture is well blended. Stir in sweetened condensed milk and cocoa.
Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches 240° using candy thermometer (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour mixture into prepared pan; cool.
When cool, cut into 44 pieces and wrap individually in Saran Wrap.

title: mushroom ring
directions: Cook butter and onions slowly until tender. Add mushrooms. Cook and stir for 5 minutes. Add seasonings and flour. Blend and add milk. Stir until thickened. Add eggs. Pour into buttered ring mold. Bake at 350° until firm (30 minutes). Good with roasts, steaks, etc.

title: overnight caramel coffee ring
directions: Grease a large Bundt pan.
Layer frozen rolls in pan.
Mix cinnamon with sugar and pour over rolls.
Layer, one at a time, chopped nuts, brown sugar and dry pudding mix.
Slice margarine and place around rolls.
Cover pan with cloth and place in warm place overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in greased baking dish with peas last. Sprinkle with cheese and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, celery, pepper and peas in a bowl.
Cover with layer of mayonnaise, sealing edges.
Sprinkle with sugar, grated cheese and bacon.
Cover tightly and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Toss and serve.
Stays crisp for 3 to 4 days.

title: armadillos
directions: Cut tops off jalapenos and remove the seeds. Mix cream cheese and Parmesan cheese together.
Stuff jalapenos with cream cheese mixture. Wrap a slice of bacon around jalapeno, starting over the open top. Secure with a wooden toothpick. Grill on barbecue until bacon is crispy.

title: caramel icing
directions: Caramelize sugar and water.
Put sugar in heavy saucepan or skillet.
Melt sugar over medium heat, stirring constantly until evenly brown.
Add water.
Stir on simmer until lumps dissolve.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Clean and slice yellow squash.
Boil with onion pieces 15 to 20 minutes and drain.
Allow to cool some and add a slightly beaten egg.
Put in a greased casserole and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients together (except optionals) and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
After baking, while cookie is still warm, you can top with a chocolate kiss or an M&M.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Boil turnips; drain well.
Combine turnips, butter, sugar and salt.
Run through blender.

title: banana fingers
directions: Cut each banana into thirds.
Dip each banana in yogurt, then roll in coconut, then roll in pecans.
Store in refrigerator. Serves 10 to 12.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix well. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes.

title: herbed carrots
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat; add garlic and saute until fragrant, about 2 minutes.
Add carrots, water and seasonings.
Cover and let simmer until crisp-tender about 10 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookie brittle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together butter, vanilla and salt in large bowl.
Gradually beat in the sugar.
Add flour, chocolate pieces and 3/4 of the nuts; mix well.
Press evenly into an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle remaining nuts over top and press in lightly.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to batter along with milk.
Add extract and pecans. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and bouillon.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Brown in melted oleo.
Put in deep casserole dish. Pour bouillon over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced tea or russian tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons or more, according to taste, to 1 cup boiling water.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add beaten egg and fruit cocktail.
Mix lightly and pour into a greased pan for baking. Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Put meat and spices in bowl. Add onion and mix well.
(If using ground turkey or chicken, you may want to add a little sage.) Place half of mixture into oblong casserole dish.
Make a row of hard boiled eggs across middle lengthwise.
Put remaining meat on top, making sure eggs are covered.
Make space around meat loaf to drain grease.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour any soup over top (mushroom is best).
Bake until sauce thickens. Slice.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add onions, buttermilk and egg. Drop by teaspoons in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Bake pie crust and cool.
Blend all the ingredients and chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cashew chicken
directions: In a wok, brown cashews in cooking oil.
Take out; reserve cashews.
Fifteen minutes prior, cut chicken into bite size pieces; add egg white, 1 teaspoon of cornstarch and 2 tablespoons of soy sauce.
Drain chicken; cook in wok until done.
While chicken is cooking, combine sugar, 1 teaspoon of cornstarch, broth, soy sauce and sherry in a bowl.
After chicken is done, add 1/3 cup of green onion and red pepper flakes and cook 30 seconds, then add sauce.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese souffl
directions: Bring milk to a boil; stir in rice, stirring constantly.
Add next 8 ingredients; stir well.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until fluffy; set aside.
Add egg yolks to cheese mixture; beat until well mixed.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into prepared souffl dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions. Spread cooked chicken in buttered baking dish. Layer broccoli and chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Spread over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: piquant stuffed eggs
directions: Mash egg yolks.
Add the fried and finely chopped bacon, minced onion, chili sauce, vinegar, salt, paprika and enough mayonnaise to make a smooth paste.
Stuff the egg whites with this mixture.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients until well mixed.
Do no use mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar. Pour into crust.
Follow in success with a layer of mashed bananas, pineapple, pecans, cherry filling and Cool Whip. Sprinkle with a few pecans on top.

title: uncle cal's pilaf
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole.
Add rice and soups; stir. Cover and microwave for 22 to 25 minutes.
Serve with side dish of sour cream.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: turtle cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex glass dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli puree with parmesan and nutmeg
directions: Cut
broccoli
stems
into 1-inch pieces; cut tops into florets.
Bring
a	large
pot
of	salted water to boil.
Add stems and cook 6 minutes.
Add florets and cook until both are very tender,
about 6 more minutes;
drain well.
Set aside 10 florets.
Place
remaining	broccoli in processor; add butter. Puree,
stopping occasionally (about 5 minutes) to scrape down sides of
bowl.
Blend
in cheese and nutmeg.
Season to taste with salt
and
pepper.
(Can
be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate
florets
and
broccoli puree separately. Bring florets
to room temperature before continuing.) Reheat broccoli puree in saucepan; garnish with broccoli florets and serve.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fry in oil until brown on each side.
Top with applesauce or sour cream.

title: extra-cheesy lasagna
directions: Combine beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet.
Cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat. Drain off drippings. Add next 6 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: lemon tart
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar and cornstarch. Gradually add milk until smooth. Cook over medium-high heat until thickened. Reduce heat. Cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Remove from heat. Stir in small amount of the hot liquid into egg yolks and return all to the pan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook 2 minutes more. (Mixture will be very thick.) Remove from the heat. Stir in butter and lemon peel. Gently stir in the lemon juice. Cover and cool completely. Fold in the sour cream. Pour into the baked pie shell. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before cutting. Garnish with whipped topping. Refrigerate the leftovers. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Grease or spray dish.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix broth and soup.
Heat and pour over chicken. Mix flour and milk.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Add Veg-All to top of chicken before adding broth to soup.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Bring to a boil and let cool:
3/4 cup vinegar, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 tablespoon water and 1 clove garlic.
Marinate the ingredients for several hours or overnight.
This will keep in the refrigerator for a week.

title: riso eleganto(an italian style shrimp and rice dish)
directions: Bring the 3 cups of broth to a boil in a saucepan which has a light fitting lid.
Add the rice; stir, cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and hold.

title: squash puffs
directions: Drain and mash squash.
Add dry ingredients.
Deep fry in hot oil for shortening (like hush puppies).

title: korean flank steak
directions: Marinate steak in soy sauce, sugar and garlic for 30 minutes. Coat with flour and dip into egg mixture with green onions.
Fry in hot oil.
Brown both sides.
Cover with foil; place in oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Bake on rack to let juices drain while cooking.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed; cool.
Slice horizontally to make 4 layers.
In large mixing bowl, combine coconut, sour cream, sugars, pineapple and vanilla.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of this mixture.
Fill cake layers with remainder.
Add Cool Whip to reserved mixture and frost cake.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours. Keeps refrigerated for several days.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat yolks separately and add to milk, making sure to mix well. Add juice, rind and salt.
Mix well and set aside.
Beat egg whites until peaks form, but not to the point that they become dry.
Gradually add sugar and beat until very stiff.
Fold egg and milk mixture into egg whites.
Turn into graham cracker crust or regular baked crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Top with whipped cream when cool.
Pie will be pale yellow, thick and creamy.
Also good with lemon juice and rind if Key limes are not available.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cook pineapple, pudding and water according to box directions. Pour into cake pan.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix up cake and pour over pudding mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill unopened can of milk in refrigerator for 3 or 4 hours. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until partially set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip chilled milk and fold into jello mixture.
Spread 1 cup of vanilla wafer crumbs over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour jello mixture over crumbs.
Pour remaining crumbs over mixture.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: apple dessert
directions: Crumble bread and mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Put in a greased casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator several hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Top with cheese during last part of baking.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter, beat together with sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until brown.
Place on rack to cool.

title: chicken gai-tao(also known as chicken with peaches)
directions: In a saucepot, place the bouillon cubes, soy sauce and water. Bring to a boil.
Add rice, cover and set aside.
Brown chicken in margarine until lightly brown on both sides.
Place the rice in a baking dish.
Place chicken and pan drippings on top of rice. Bake (covered tightly) at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Arrange peaches on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Put back in oven (covered) for 10 to 15 minutes (until peaches are warm).

title: baked beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 3-quart casserole for 3 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix well and float lemon, orange or fresh strawberries on top.

title: corn cakes
directions: Combine corn meal, salt, sugar and onions with water and mix well.
Grease a heavy griddle over medium heat until a drop of water sizzles on it.
Place large spoonfuls mixture on hot griddle to form small cakes.
Cook about 3 minutes and turn.
Cook until golden brown.

title: spicy green enchiladas
directions: Cook onions with garlic in 1 tablespoon oil until soft.
When finished, add a pinch of salt.
Heat salad oil over medium heat and dip tortillas in for a few seconds on both sides.
Drain and cool.
Dice tofu into small pieces and grate cheese.
Along middle of each tortilla, place onions, cheese and tofu and roll up.
Put tortillas in a greased baking pan, seams down.
Drain spinach and liquify in a blender along with green onions, peppers and soup. You may need to add a bit of water if too thick.
Pour 3/4 of sauce over enchiladas and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When ready to serve, top with remainder of sauce and sprinkle with tomatoes and sour cream, if desired.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine all except flour and butter and bring to a boil.
Melt butter in small skillet; stir in flour.
Add to corn mixture. Pour into casserole and top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: louisiana hush puppies
directions: Blend corn, onion and jalapenos only lightly.
Add all dry ingredients and mix, being sure mixture holds together.
If it doesn't, add more meal and be sure to stir well.
After mixing, drop each hush puppy from a teaspoon into the hot peanut oil and fry until as brown as desired.
Don't make them too big so they will cook better.
Recipe makes a lot, but they can be reheated. Also, they freeze very well.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Bring Jell-O and applesauce to boiling.
Add thawed raspberries and juice.
Put in mold or small casserole dish and refrigerate to jell.
Recipe can be doubled and put in large Pyrex flat dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into bite size balls.
Put into baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: curry chicken and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot except rice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover for 30 minutes.
Add rice and continue to cook until rice and chicken are done.
Add water if needed.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar and beat until smooth.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Fold in either whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker crust and chill 3 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/3 cups boiling water over 1 cup oats; cover and let set 20 minutes.
Mix brown sugar, white sugar and 1/2 cup butter, then add oats, vanilla and eggs.
Mix and add flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot marmalade
directions: Cook squash in water for 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain squash.
Return to stove and add sugar, pineapple, lemon juice. Cook 6 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in dry jello until dissolved.
Put in hot jars and seal with wax.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cream cheese together. Add 1 cup hot water, a little at
a time, until well dissolved.
Add diluted orange juice; mix well. Add pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix well. Let set until jelled. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except sausage and cheese.
Add these last.
Pour into large rectangular buttered casserole dish. (Recipe can be doubled.) Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Let stand before cutting.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Saute onion.
Stir in tomato sauce, eggs, cheese, bread crumbs, salt and thyme.
Add ground beef and pork.
Mix well. Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put together in layers in order.
Salad should set in refrigerator 18 to 24 hours before serving.

title: soto ayam kuning(indonesian chicken soup)
directions: Heat the water in a large pot until hot, but not boiling. Add the beans and ham hocks and adjust the heat so the water barely bubbles. Simmer slowly, covered, for 3 hours, stirring occasionally, and adjusting the heat if necessary to keep the liquid from boiling. Remove the ham hocks and remove the meat from the bones. Chop the meat into bite-sized pieces and discard the bones. Using a potato masher, roughly mash the beans in the kettle. The soup should be lumpy. Return the meat to the pot. If the soup seems too thin, boil, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently, until the soup has thickened slightly. Saut the onions in a heavy skillet in the butter over moderate heat until richly browned, 10 to 15 minutes. Add the browned onions to the soup and continue to cook, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fantastic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend together first 6 ingredients.
Add 4 cups flour and soda mix.
Add remaining flour and chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken. Cook for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peach waldorf salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine chopped peaches, sliced celery, walnuts, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt to taste.
Toss until well combined.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Separate lettuce leaves; rinse in cold water.
Dry on paper towels or in salad spinner.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix until smooth.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in loaf pan.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator for about 10 minutes or until bowl is cool.
Beat in orange sherbet with mixer.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Pour into jello mold or glass dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rich chewy brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate, then cool.
Beat eggs and sugar, then add chocolate and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Spoon into greased 9-inch square pan or an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well, store in airtight container.
Mix 3 to 4 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli according to package; omit salt. Saute onions in margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In large bowl, combine corn meal, soda and salt; stir and set aside.
In food processor, process cheese, onions, garlic and peppers.
Mix together all ingredients with corn meal mixture. Pour into large skillet (hot, oiled and sprinkled with corn meal). Bake in 400° oven until knife will come out clean in center.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes.
Coconut and raisins are optional.

title: brickle bread
directions: Mix all together for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 300° and finish baking for 45 minutes.

title: bette's strawberry salad
directions: Mix everything together except for sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in large pyrex dish and let chill.
Spread sour cream over layer.
Pour remainder of mixture on top. Chill.

title: sunday special-potato bake
directions: Wash potatoes and boil until tender.
Cool, peel and dice. Combine next 6 ingredients and mix with potatoes.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir.
Cover with crunched chips and bacon.
Bake another 15 minutes.
Makes at least 12 generous servings.

title: shaker bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in Dutch oven or soup kettle.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.

title: james' favorite oysters
directions: Fry bacon until
done.	Save
some fat to fry onion in. When onion is tender,
put oysters in and let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Eat over corn bread or rice.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Oil skillet with cooking oil.
Heat 1 minute.
Stir-fry chicken in 2 batches until browned; remove from skillet.
Oil skillet; stir-fry vegetables until tender, but crisp.
Add soup, water, soy sauce and ginger; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet; heat through.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and yolks.
Sift and add flour with bananas, milk and add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in stiff egg whites. Bake 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: kraut salad
directions: Put corn and kraut in large bowl.
Cut up celery, onion, carrots and pepper and add to kraut and corn.
Then add sugar, oil,
salt to taste. vinegar and pimentos.
Stir well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion; cook in a small amount of water until nearly tender.
Drain and mash.
Add cheese, butter, egg and crackers.
Put into greased dish.
Top with layer of crushed crackers and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown on top (about 15 minutes).

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and milk.
Stir well.
Add Velveeta and stir until melted.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Let set for a few minutes.

title: easy cannoli filling
directions: Beat Ricotta cheese with powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add chocolate chips.
Fill shells.
Dip ends in nuts and top with powdered sugar.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking powder, salt and sugar and sift again 3 times. Add butter. Combine egg, milk and vanilla. Add to flour mixture, stirring until all flour is dampened; then beat vigorously 1 minute. Melt 4 tablespoons butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or 8-inch skillet over low flame. Add brown sugar (1/4 teaspoon nutmeg may be mixed with brown sugar, if desired). Stir until melted. On this, arrange peach slices. Turn batter over contents of pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes or until done. Loosen cake from sides of pan with spatula. Serve upside down with peaches on top. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix all together and put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: beignets(french fritters)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat egg and milk together and pour into dry ingredients.
Add banana and mix with electric mixer.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot grease and fry until golden brown.
Don't get grease too hot as they will be raw inside. Shake in a paper bag with powdered sugar and serve while hot.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour over meat and allow to stand in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from marinade and place in shallow baking pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally with marinade.
After 1/2 hour remove excess fat.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: Cream together the milk, eggs, sugar and cream cheese. Gradually add the rest of the ingredients.
Make sure there are no lumps.
Stir it all well; must be well blended.
Put half of the batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread your favorite fruit preserves over the batter, then pour the remaining batter over the preserves.

title: cucumber salad ring
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese, salad dressing, horseradish and salt.
Beat until smooth and add lemon juice. Chill until partially set.
Stir in cucumber and onions.
Put in mold.
Chill.
(Double this recipe for a party.)

title: fresh fruit with honey sour cream dip
directions: Makes 1 1/4 cups sauce.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
Wash snails; add to pot, including wash water.
Dump in carrots.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Salt and pepper.
Cook over fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
Serves 3,800.
(If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added.
But do this only in an emergency; most people do not like hare in their stew.)

title: grilled barbecue fish
directions: Put fish fillets in aluminum pan.
Top with rest of ingredients.
Grill until done (fish is flaky).
(We use on gas grill.)

title: chicken booyah
directions: Cook chicken in 2 quarts of water and 1 tablespoon salt until chicken is tender and can easily be removed from bone.
Remove chicken from broth. Put vegetables (not peas) in broth and cook until tender.
Then add chicken meat and tomato juice and season to taste.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry pudding-pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg. Beat in flour until blended. Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Spread evenly in greased pie plate. Bake at 350° (if glass plate, 325°) for 45 minutes or until firm and golden.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine; add to crumbs and sugar.
Press into pan. Soften cream cheese and mix well.
Add milk, eggs, salt and lemon juice.
Pour over crumb crust.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: white bread(2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Scald milk.
Pour in large bowl. Add sugar, salt and butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Beat in egg.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Knead 10 minutes.
Grease large bowl.
Add dough.
Let rise in warm place (85°) until double.
Punch down.
Divide in half.
Rest under bowl 15 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Place in buttered bread pan.
Return to warm place.
Let rise to 1-inch above pan. Bake at 350° on lower rack of oven until golden brown.
Turn out on rack.
Brush with melted butter.
Enjoy.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla, then add self-rising flour.
Mix well.
Add apples and pecans; mix well.
Pour or dip mixture into a well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: onion chicken stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup mix, cornstarch, ginger and water.
Set aside.
In 10-inch skillet or wok, over medium-high heat, in hot oil, stir-fry half of chicken until chicken is browned and no longer pink.
Remove and set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Spoon off fat.
Return chicken to skillet. Stir in soup mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli, mushrooms and carrots.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with rice.
Garnish with cilantro if desired.
Makes about 6 cups or 4 main dish servings.
Prep time: 10 minutes; cook time: 15 minutes.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Peel and cube fine the potatoes.
In a 2-quart pot or microwave dish, steam all vegetables with broth and salt until tender.
Combine flour, margarine and milk in a shaker container. Stir into vegetables, bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: edith's corn pudding
directions: Stir together corn, sugar and salt.
Beat 5 eggs and mix in half and half.
Combine and mix.
Put butter and paprika on top. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after first 15 minutes and sprinkle more paprika on top.

title: chicken with yellow rice
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken.
Place chicken in baking dish and pour heated soup and water on top.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
While chicken cooks, cook rice separately accordingly to package directions.
