After rice is cooked, place it under chicken and cook an additional 30 minutes uncovered.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Grease large baking dish.
Place ingredients in pan in order listed, pouring tomato sauce over top.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Take cover off for last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: toasted spice cake
directions: Blend shortening, 2 cups brown sugar, vanilla and egg yolks. Dissolve baking soda in sour milk.
Separately, sift flour and dry ingredients together four times.
All in one good beating, add sour milk and dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add 1 cup brown sugar.
Spread on top of raw cake and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake passes toothpick test.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine together until crumbly.
Then press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: apricot bars
directions: Stir together the flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cardamon; set aside.
Stir together the applesauce, orange juice, oil and egg whites until combined.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until combined.
Stir in apricots.
Spread in ungreased pan (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: sunshine kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine mix, egg, oil and water. Mixture will be dry. Scoop dough with teaspoon. Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 13 min., until brown.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift 2 cups flour and the powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes until lightly browned.
Beat together eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Sift together remaining flour and baking powder and stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 30.

title: apple butter
directions: Put apples in large kettle with 3 gallons of water and cook until sauce.
Add vinegar and sugar; boil 3 hours.
Add spices to suit your taste.

title: peach delight
directions: Bring your pineapple, water and sugar to a boil, remove and add jello.
Chill until partially set.
Whip this mixture before adding next ingredients.

title: chicken and tortilla
directions: Bone and cut chicken into large pieces.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips and then in half.
Mix soup, sour cream, broth, onion and green chili.
Butter a large casserole and make layers: 1/2 tortillas; 1/2 chicken; 1/2 sliced mushrooms; 1/2 soup mixture; 1/2 cheese; repeat.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn bread and butter.
Melt butter and stir in corn bread mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch round baking dish (2 inches deep).
Combine melted butter, oil, parsley, cheese, thyme and salt in small bowl.
Cut potatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Overlap 1/2 the slices in prepared dish.
Spoon on 1/2 the butter mixture. Repeat the layers.
Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together. Cook at 400° until done.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to sour milk (to which soda has been added) to sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla and black walnuts.

title: lipton beef goulash
directions: In Dutch oven, heat shortening; brown meat well.
Stir in onion soup mix, tomato paste and water.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender, adding more water if needed. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: baked eggplant with tomatoes
directions: Wash and halve eggplants lengthwise. Sprinkle inside eggplants lightly with salt to reduce bitterness. Let rest 15 to 30 minutes. Wipe with paper towel. Sprinkle with garlic and herb seasoning. Spray a large baking dish with olive oil spray or oil with small amount of olive oil. Pour one can diced tomatoes in dish. Cut eggplants lengthwise from the tops, leaving connected at tops. Place sliced onions in the slits of eggplants and place in dish. Spoon second can of tomatoes over top of eggplants. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Heat soups.
Add mayonnaise, bell pepper and mushrooms. Assemble in layers in greased casserole:
noodles, asparagus, chicken, soup and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Add almonds on top. Bake until hot and bubbly at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy fantasy fudge
directions: Mix butter, sugar, and milk; bring to rolling boil on medium heat; stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes on medium; remove from heat.
Gradually add chips until melted; add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased pan.

title: barry's pizza casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain. Sprinkle with seasoning.
Add all other ingredients except the cheese.
Cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes. Add cheese. Cover and heat until cheese is melted.

title: blueberry sponge cake(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Lightly grease a 15 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Line bottom with waxed paper and grease again.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar at high speed until foamy.
Add 1/3 cup of the sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating constantly until whites are glossy and stand in soft peaks.

title: chicken cordon gold
directions: Spread cheese on chicken; add 1 slice ham.
Roll jelly roll fashion and fold in side; secure with toothpick.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: fruit pizza(low calorie)
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8 inch slices and line pizza pan. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until brown. Let cool. Then mix together cream cheese, Splenda and vanilla. When ready to serve, top with fresh strawberries, bananas, pineapple, blueberries, etc. (your choice). Make sure to dip bananas in lemon juice to keep them from browning.
About 140 calories and 5 grams of fat.

title: banana milk
directions: In a saucepan heat up milk until warm.
Add vanilla and spices.
Remove from stove and pour into blender.
Add bananas and blend for 30 seconds.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugar and cool.
Add eggs, sifted dry ingredients, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Top with chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: This dish goes well with sweet potato and apple casserole. Place dried beef on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Roll chicken breast up and wrap each in one slice of bacon.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: heavenly bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, corn syrup, and 2 c. peanut butter over heat and melt together.
Add Rice Krispies and 1/2 of pudding.
Put in jelly roll pan.
Beat together margarine, powdered sugar, milk and remaining pudding.
Spread over first layer and chill.
Melt together remaining peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Frost. Chill.

title: coca-cola pot roast
directions: Brown the roast in oil.
Drain off fat.
Combine the ingredients.
Pour over meat; cover.
Simmer about 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Thicken gravy and serve over sliced meat. Serves 6.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Bring to boil water, margarine, oil and cocoa.
Pour over dry ingredients, mixing well.
Mix together buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to chocolate batter.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Start icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: zesty breaded chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in soup mix combined with bread crumbs.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until chicken tests done and is brown.
Cook on lower shelf.
Spray pan with cooking spray before adding coated chicken, then spray chicken.
Be generous with the spray.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Lace ribs on spit accordian style, using holding forks. Adjust on rotisserie above drip pan.
Let ribs rotate over slow coals.
Cook onion in hot oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
After ribs cook for 40 minutes, baste well with the sauce, and add damp hickory to coals.
Cook for 20 minutes longer or until well done.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, then other fresh veggies in a large bowl.
Layer the peas and dressing (2 cups mayo and 2 tablespoons sugar).
Top with cheese.
Cover; allow to chill overnight.
Add bacon just before tossing.

title: pecan tussies
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour.
Make 1 inch balls and press into small muffin tins.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise in a medium size bowl and mix thoroughly.
Add onion, mustard, crab meat, garlic powder and parsley; mix well.
Best if chilled overnight.
Serve with crackers, bread or even snack sticks.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn, until smooth.
Add corn. Spoon into greased casserole dish and place dish into pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: complete salad
directions: Mix and pour dressing over top.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown chuck and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato soup until mixed, then add green beans.
Heat for a few minutes until hot. Put into greased casserole dish and top with mashed potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: triple bean salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except salad oil. Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Just before serving, drain well.
Toss with salad oil.

title: green bean salad with basil vinaigrette
directions: Cook beans in a large pot of rapidly boiling salted water until just crisp-tender.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Transfer to bowl. Combine shallots and vinegar.
Gradually mix in oil. Add basil.
Add enough dressing to beans to coat.
Gently mix in 2/3 cup cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
(Can be made 4 hours ahead.
Cover and chill.) Place beans on platter. Top with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scottish scones
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter.
Add beaten eggs, cream and raisins.
Mix and knead a little.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in greased pan at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix chocolate, milk, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook to 235° or soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add pumpkin; blend well.
Mix dry ingredients together; beat into egg, sugar and pumpkin mixture.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan; bake for 15 minutes.
When done, invert on towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll cake and towel together into roll; cool 10 minutes.
Unroll and spread with cream cheese and Cool Whip that have been blended together.
Reroll and refrigerate.

title: autumn pumpkin torte
directions: First Layer: Mix together first 4 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes; cool.

title: rice cheeseburger
directions: Follow package instructions; prepare instant rice with water. Blend rice with all other ingredients, except cheese.
Shape mixture by hand, forming patties around a generous spoonful of shredded cheese.
Patties may be fried or baked.
Serve with usual condiments on toasted split rolls.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel.
Cut into medium size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in large casserole dish. Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until cheese is melted.
Stir and serve.

title: cherry pie filling(to can)
directions: Select very ripe, firm cherries.
Rinse and pit cherries and hold in cold water.
To prevent browning, you may use ascorbic acid in cold water.
Combine clear jel, sugar and cinnamon in large kettle.
Add water, food coloring and almond extract if desired.
Stir mixture and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add lemon juice and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Fold in cherries and fill mixture without delay into clean jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Process pints or quarts 30 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: easy taco pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls into a 9-inch pie pan.
Cook ground beef with one package taco seasoning.
Spread cooked meat over roll crust.
Spread sour cream over meat.
Sprinkle generously with grated cheese and top with crushed corn chips.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: easy soup
directions: Bring soup mix, bouillon cubes and water to a boil.
Add spaghetti and potatoes.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brandy's peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients and cook until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Take off heat; add peanut butter, vanilla and butter.
Pour into buttered glass baking dish.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: mocha sauce
directions: Dissolve instant coffee in hot water.
Beat egg yolks with sugar and salt.
Add coffee; cook in a double boiler, stirring constantly until custard is very thick.
Cool.
Chill in refrigerator.
Fold in whipped cream just before serving.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Layer crispy crowns in bottom of pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown and drain ground beef.
In a bowl, mix soup, milk, 1 cup cheese, 1/2 can fried onions, pepper and garlic powder. Pour ground beef over potatoes.
Add broccoli and tomato.
Pour soup mixture over that and bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Add remaining cheese and onions and bake for 3 to 4 minutes, uncovered.

title: ginger ale punch
directions: Boil water and sugar to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Add juices. When ready to serve add 1 1/2 quarts ginger ale.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat blackberries, water and 1 cup sugar to boiling.
Combine and mix well the flour, cinnamon, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Pour in batter and spread evenly.
Pour in berry mix (boiling hot).
Bake in a 375° oven until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: malt cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Topping.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Place pecan halves in a pattern in bottom of unbaked pastry shell.
Beat eggs slightly; mix in corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Gently pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; lower temperature to 350° and cook an additional 30 to 35 minutes (filling should be slightly less set in center than around edge).
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple with marshmallows; set aside. Combine egg, pineapple juice, sugar, flour and vinegar in a saucepan; cook and stir on medium heat until slightly thick. Let cool. When cool, combine with Cool Whip, then fold in marshmallow mixture. Add chopped apples and 1 cup peanuts. Mix carefully. Sprinkle top with remaining peanuts.

title: leftover mashed potatoes
directions: Whip potatoes again, enough to handle with hands.
Season. Make into a large patty (or several smaller patties).
Put on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add broccoli, green pepper, onions, olives and carrots to spaghetti.
Sprinkle generously with garlic salt.
Mix dressing according to instructions and pour over pasta; toss well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours to absorb flavors. Serve with crackers or toasted bread.

title: frog eye fruit salad
directions: Mix.
Combine
and cook until thick.
Cool.
Boil 1 box acini pepe
macaroni for 8 minutes with oil and a little salt added
to water.
Drain.
Pour
cooked,
cooled
mixture over macaroni
and add to refrigerated mixture.
Blend well together.
Refrigerate until ready to dish out and serve.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Put cut rhubarb in pie shell.
Beat eggs, salt, sugar and flour until creamy.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned tea cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat til fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk.
If still sticky, add more flour.
roll out on floured board and cutwith cookie cutters. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375 degrees for 8 minutes til top is slightly firm, but not brown.
Ice with powdered sugar glaze as desired.

title: english peas casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir in peas and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Shred cheese and combine with sausage and Bisquick with your hands.
Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Make the balls
small, since they increase as they are baked. Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes.
Or, shape into balls and freeze. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 100 small balls. Serve warm with toothpicks.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix dry cake mix and dry pudding mix.
Add eggs and oil.
Add hot water and poppy seeds.
Blend well.
Bake in 3 small loaf pans at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make yellow cake mix.
Beat the pudding, milk and cream cheese 3 minutes.
Add to the top of the cake.
Then add drained can of crushed pineapple.
Top with container of Cool Whip.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks.
Add nuts, chocolate chips, vanilla and salt. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet covered with foil.
Put in a preheated 350° oven that is turned off.
Leave overnight in oven.

title: chicken salad
directions: Beat until thick, using rotary beater.
Do not use electric beater.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix 2 sticks butter, water and 4 tablespoons cocoa together. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and while hot add 2 cups sugar, flour, salt, eggs, soda and sour cream.
Beat until smooth and bake in greased and floured 11 1/2 x 17-inch pan and bake at 325° until done.

title: fish batter recipe
directions: Beat egg yolk and fold into other ingredients.
Fry in deep-fat.

title: chicken salads
directions: Steam raisins until plump. Combine with chicken, celery, nuts, apples and pineapple. Moisten with mayonnaise. Mix lightly with 2 forks. Serve in crisp lettuce cups. Serve with mayonnaise. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheddar dijon cheese ball
directions: With a hand mixer or blender, mix the cheeses, margarine and mustard until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a bowl.
Cover. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours until firm.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Makes 2 cups.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine broth, onion and sweet pepper. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until onion and sweet pepper are tender.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Mix soups together with rice, oleo, and can of milk.
Heat until warm.
Pour half into 9 x 13 baking dish.
On top put chicken breast, then rest of mixture.
Sprinkle with small amount of cheese.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Combine flour, butter and milk in a saucepan to make white sauce.
Put saucepan over medium heat and stir until thickened. Add salt, pepper and sherry.
Remove from heat and add crab meat. Pour into buttered casserole and sprinkle cheese over top.
Cook in 450° oven until cheese melts.
Do not overcook!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix with melted margarine.
Put half of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with pieces of cooked chicken.
I use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together soup, broth and sour cream and pour mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle remainder of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool cake.

title: chile verde con carne
directions: Cut steak into inch size pieces.
Flour and brown lightly in oil.
Add salt.
Add diced onions, cook until soft and clear. Peel tomatoes.
Slice and add to mixture with enough water to cover.
Mash garlic and add chiles and liquid.
Add peeled chopped potatoes.
Simmer until meat is tender and potatoes are done.
Usually it takes about 45 minutes.
Little liquid should remain.
Serve with flour tortillas.

title: easy hamburger helper
directions: Brown and season hamburger meat.
Boil macaroni until done. Drain.
Mix in butter, milk and cheese.
Add hamburger meat and corn to macaroni and cheese.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine and Velveeta cheese over low heat.
Mix in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in 2 (1 pound) boxes confectioners sugar.
Pour in buttered container.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Layer rice, broccoli, onions and cheese in a greased 8-inch square dish.
Spread soup over top.
Drizzle water over casserole. Bake uncovered 350° 45 minutes.
For meal-in-one-casserole place 1-1/2 cups of chopped cooked chicken over broccoli layer.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and mash.
Heat margarine, cheese, milk and salt over low heat; add to mashed potatoes.
Fold in beaten eggs.
Put into greased 9 x 13 inch pan Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45
minutes.

title: butterscotch circles
directions: Shake all ingredients, pour into freezable containers and freeze until solid.
Serves 12.

title: poppy seed chicken 1
directions: Boil chicken; debone and chop.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and sour cream and spread over chicken. Melt oleo and mix with crushed crackers and place over.
Sprinkle poppy seed over this and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Bake cranberries at 350 degrees until popping open. Let cool and add sugar and brandy. Stir. Chill and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cheese and green onions.
Add other ingredients. Form into ball. Roll in pecan chips and chill.

title: easy baked meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Mix ground beef, bread, sage and seasoning.
Shape into balls and put in large baking pan.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine flour and baking powder. Set aside. Cream the butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture in 3 parts, alternating with milk.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Fold in chocolate chips. Bake in greased tube pan in a 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: cornsticks or corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together egg, milk, butter and oil.
Add, all at once, to dry ingredients.
Pour batter into hot, greased pan, filling about 2/3 full.
Put in oven.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake corn bread in a shallow pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Put fruit (bite size) all together in large bowl.
Serve dip along side or pour on individual servings.
Try it! You'll like it!

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water; heat and thicken over heat.
Cool.
Add lemon juice.
Pour over berries in shell or add berries to liquid.
Put in shell.
Crumb top or pie crust top. Bake at 400° until pie bubbling and done.
Crush few blueberries in cornstarch to color.

title: mushroom-sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole and set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, drain well and sprinkle sausage over croutons.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients, mix well and pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with tomatoes and parsley, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: lentil soup
directions: Dice and brown sausage a little and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook until lentils and barley are soft, maybe 1 hour or so.

title: window cleaner
directions: Alfalfa:
Make like a tea.
Use 1 teaspoon to 8 ounces of water.
This is good for allergies, blood purifier, arthritis, cancer, diabetes, fatigue and kidney cleaner.

title: lone star stew
directions: Fry bacon, then set aside.
In a large stew pot, sear stew meat, lower heat and add tomatoes, beef broth, water, celery, onions, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add salt, pepper and seasoned salt; then add carrots and potatoes.
Cook about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Then add corn and crumbled bacon.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Serve with plenty of cornbread.

title: sweet pickles(shelley's favorite)
directions: Open quart of pickles and drain off liquid.
Slice all pickles into 3/16-inch slices.
Put 1/2 of the slices back into jar.
Pour in 1 cup sugar and pickling spice.
Put in rest of the sliced pickles.
Add rest of the sugar and stir as well as you can.

title: brown 'n serve pizza
directions: Measure warm water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in Fleischmann's active dry yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt, peanut oil and 1 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.

title: easy chicken and gravy
directions: Combine soups.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
The gravy is delicious served over mashed potatoes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill 5-quart crock-pot heaping full with apples.
Drizzle 4 cups sugar over apples (or less, depends on sweetness of apples). Sprinkle cinnamon, cloves and salt over apples.
Cover with lid. Lid may not fit tightly at start, but apples will shrink while cooking.
Begin cooking on high, then lower heat and cook all day until thick and dark.
Put in jars and seal (stir occasionally while cooking).

title: 3 bean bake
directions: In a large casserole, layer beans in the order given.
In a skillet, cook bacon, remove, crumble and sprinkle over beans.
In 2 tablespoons of the drippings, saute onion until tender.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and margarine together.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil this mixture for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and stir in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir ingredients until mixture is creamy and smooth.
(An electric mixer may be used.) Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Allow to cool and cut as desired.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and bubbles. Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: "herman" starter
directions: In a large ceramic or glass bowl (don't use metal), dissolve yeast in water.
Add flour and sugar and beat with whisk until smooth.
Cover loosely and leave at room temperature 48 hours. Makes 2 cups of Starter dough.
Use 1 cup for Herman coffee cake or other recipes and give the other to a friend.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Add peanut butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken in a basket
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, onion soup mix, rice and milk together.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Mix Stove Top stuffing mix according to directions.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and brown stuffing.

title: spanish rice
directions: Dice bacon and cook until crisp.
Remove from pan and cook onions and green pepper in pan.
Add rice and saute for 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, water, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Cover and simmer over low heat, approximately one hour.
Add bacon and cook together.

title: fast fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add water and butter and blend.
Add vanilla.
Frosts top and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: golden fruit salad dressing
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add fruit juices and sugar.
Slightly beat egg yolks.
Add to mixture in double boiler. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream just before serving.
This makes a very good dressing for fresh fruit.

title: mrs. hammett's date cake
directions: Chop dates; cover with boiling water and add soda.
Cream sugar and shortening; add egg, vanilla and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Add cooled date mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups sifted flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well; bake in well-greased pan at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: aunt viv's vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Grate first four ingredients and drain, reserving juice. Dissolve Knox gelatin in small amount of water to soften.
Heat drained juice in microwave, add 1/4 c. of this juice to gelatin and stir this into the mayonnaise, mix, then add to the drained vegetables.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread over your favorite sandwich bread.

title: sweet-sour wieners
directions: Cut wieners in julienne strips.
Brown wieners in small amount of hot fat; drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Mix vinegar with dry ingredients.
Add pineapple syrup and water; add mixture to skillet.
Cook and stir until it begins to thicken.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
(More water may be added if needed.)
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Serve over hot rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and cook over low heat 30 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally. Serve with rice.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: mom's cole slaw dressing
directions: Shake the vinegar and sugar together.
Shake the cream and oil together.
Add mayonnaise to consistency.

title: taco salad
directions: Wash and chop lettuce in advance.
Place lettuce in a colander so that all moisture can drip out before preparing the salad. Place colander in refrigerator.
Crumble the ground sirloin and cook over medium heat until just done.
Put the chopped lettuce, diced tomatoes, cooked warm sirloin and 3/4 cup of the grated cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Add your favorite dressing and toss well.
Divide the salad on 6 plates.
Sprinkle remaining 3/4 cup cheese evenly on top of each serving.
Put 1 1/2 teaspoons of sour cream on top of each salad.
I like to serve this with toasted tortilla triangles.
Serves 6.

title: creamed peas and new potatoes
directions: Steam new potatoes about 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Combine peas, salt and sugar in saucepan with water to cover. Cook, uncovered, 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Return peas to pan. Add butter and green onions to peas.
Heat until butter melts.
Add potatoes. Add pepper and cream.
Heat through, but do not cook.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each breast with piece of bacon.
Secure with toothpicks. Cover bottom of flat greased 8 x 12 x 12-inch baking dish with dried beef.
Arrange breasts on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.

title: german chocolate caramel squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture to butter and sugar along with eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Chill dough about one hour.
Roll very thin and use a tin can to cut out cookie shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle baked cookie with a little sugar.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: mrs. eisenhower's million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk in large saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 6 minutes.
Meanwhile, place remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour cooked mixture into bowl with chocolate bits and marshmallow and beat until chocolate bits and marshmallow are melted.
Stir in chopped nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 14 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: bill's pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain beans and rinse.
Put beans, garlic, onion, salt and pepper in a 3-quart pot, cover with water, boil for 5 minutes, stirring.
Add pork chops and boil for 3-1/2 minutes while stirring.
Reduce heat to a simmer and cook 3 hours, stirring from time to time.
Remove chops from pot and with a fork, shred meat and remove bone.
Return meat to pot.
Adjust seasonings.
Serve with chopped onions, cornbread and sliced ham or with warm flour tortillas, cheese and salsa.
Enjoy!

title: ramona's breakfast loaf
directions: Cut bread about 3/4-inch from bottom lengthwise; hollow out top.
Combine sausage, cheese, egg and bread crumbs.
Work together with hands.
Place mixture in top of French bread.
Put bottom back on; wrap in tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Slice to serve.

title: hermits
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and stir with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in oblong pan (13 x 9-inch).
Test with toothpick.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease/spray 9 x 13 baking pan and put bread in bottom of pan. Beat eggs; add milk, mustard and salt and mix. Alternate layers of sausage and cheese on bread cubes. Pour egg mixture over sausage and cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook noodles in rapidly boiling, salted water, stirring occasionally until tender.
Drain.
While noodles cook, mix 2 tablespoons melted butter, cottage cheese, sour cream, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add mixture to drained noodles and spoon into a greased casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and remaining 2 tablespoons butter, stirring well.
Sprinkle over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening and add buttermilk; roll out biscuits and place on baking sheet. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
This recipe will serve 7 people.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in a large shallow pan over low heat.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Add cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Mix over low heat until pieces are covered.
Cook 45 minutes in oven, stirring every 15 minutes. Makes approximately 7 1/2 cups.

title: pink party punch
directions: Mix boiling water into gelatin.
Mix until gelatin dissolves, then add cold water, fruit juices and sugar.
Put in freezer until icy; stir and add ginger ale.
Makes 25 to 30 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: *You can also use bacon or sausage.
If you do, be sure to cook meat well and drain before putting into casserole.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: If making more than a 2 layer cake, just add a little more of all ingredients.

title: soda cracker pralines
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to rolling boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Add finely crushed soda crackers and drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well and form 2 logs or 1 ball shape. Roll in chopped pecans. Chill and serve.

title: pecan tassies(makes 24)
directions: Cheese Pastry:
Let cream cheese and margarine stick soften at room temperature.
Blend.
Stir in flour.
Make into a ball and wrap with Saran or wax paper to seal.
Chill slightly (about 1 hour).
Shape into two dozen balls (about 1-inch).
Place in 1 3/4-inch ungreased muffin tins.
Press dough against bottom and sides of cup.

title: seafood spread
directions: Spread cream cheese on serving plate.
Spread sauce over cheese, then spread crab over the sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips in a saucepan until cheese has melted.
Add chips; put in baking dish and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine green beans and cream of mushroom soup.
Put in appropriate sized baking dish.
Add enough milk to come halfway up baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven. Add Durkee onions, sprinkled on top.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients (except cheese).
Pour into 6 x 10-inch greased pan or casserole dish. Bake 35 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together the margarine, sugar and eggs. Add the remaining ingredients, mixing well. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: meat pie
directions: Cook onion in skillet with a little water to soften.
Add ground turkey and spices; cook turkey, breaking it up.
Add water with bouillon cube.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first in a bowl. Add liquid ingredients next. Mix all ingredients together. Add fruit. Stir a little. Can fruit (303 size). Bake at 350° until brown. Serves 6 people.

title: souper sausage corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine soup, eggs and milk.
Stir in corn muffin mix just until blended.
Gently fold in sausage.
Spoon corn muffin mixture into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serve warm.

title: dill sauce for fish
directions: Combine dill with parsley and blend with white sauce.
Cook over very low heat or in double boiler for about 5 minutes.
Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: aunt betty's sugar cookies
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add sifted
dry
ingredients with milk or cream.
Roll out on floured wax
paper
to
1/4-inch thick.
Cut with any desired cookie cutters.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° until edges just start to turn brown, 12 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix and pour all the above ingredients into a deep dish pie crust.
Top with a regular pie crust, leaving pan on.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove top pan and bake for 15 more minutes, or until brown.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Bring hamburger to a boil in 7 cups water.
Add diced onion, 3 bouillon cubes, Veg-All, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil, then add 1 cup orzo and simmer 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip mini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, sugar, and baking powder together in bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Add egg, milk, and oil.
Mix. Add chocolate chips.
Stir.
Spray mini muffin pans with cooking spray, then add mixture.
Bake at 300° for 15-20 minutes until lightly golden brown.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container.
Blend first on medium, then on high speed until creamy.
Store in a covered glass jar, refrigerated.
Keeps well for 2 weeks or more.
Shake well before serving.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spoon into mini-muffin pan. Bake at 375° for 12-14 minutes. Yield 48-60 muffins.

title: icebox cake
directions: In a large bowl or serving dish, layer the bottom with 1/3 of the angel food cake, broken up.
Prepare pudding, then spread 1/3 of it on top of cake pieces.
Prepare Dream Whip, spread 1/3 of it on pudding.
Next, add 1/3 candy pieces.
Repeat these layers 2 more times.
